name: Wayne Schoeneberg
text: Unforgettable, remarkable, customer for life. I just got back with a family of five from 4 days of skiing in mammoth mountain. Being the sole person that had to arrange everything using BTS made the process smooth, easy, accommodating and fantastic. I haven't been skiing in 20 years and this was my first time back with small kids and seniors some who have never skied before. The whole staff was incredible and unbelievably over the top, friendly, helpful and nice. It's rare to find service like this these days. I am a VERY hard customer to please. Nothing EVER goes right for me and being in business for my self I am extremely critical of any little thing that goes wrong, from a crooked uniform, personal appearance, a slip of the tongue, a roll of the eyes, or a hint of a bad attitude none of that was present when dealing with this organization. They bent over backwards in being available, handling special requests, dealing with my problems, last minute changes and making me feel like I was their best and only customer on the entire mountain. Like a few of the others I rarely write reviews, however these people more than exceeded expectations and totally blew me away. I want to go out of my way to tell you this place is - PHE-NOM-A-NAL!!!

resp.text: Thanks so much for your business and the wonderful review. Our goal is always to create a customer for life, so we are thrilled to hear that we achieved that goal. We are very proud of our amazing staff and it is great to hear they were able to provide such a positive experience for your family. We look forward to hearing from you in the future.

text: I would compare my experience with this store to buying paint from Walmart. I was able to look past the poor customers service because some of our friends had mentioned a few colors from Dunn-Edwards.  We were finishing up a project and I stopped by to grab some swatches, but they had already locked the doors.  It was 12:55 PM according to my iPhone, a very accurate time.  The employee standing there, probably the one who had locked the door, would not turn his head.  I would have been in the store 3 minutes prior, but I had to drive around to find parking because they've marked off about 10 empty spots in the front of their store for "employees only".  As I walked to my car, I noticed employees walking out of the back and hopping in their cars, parked in the unmarked spots.  Next time, I'll just go to Lowes.  They carry better paint anyways (Sherwin Williams).

The place is big and cool. Pet friendly. Live band. Only thing I didn’t really like is too many kids running around crazy. It’s like they are drunk of the non alcoholic one! This is where all the mommies go and let their kids run wild! I don’t blame them, it’s because it’s delicious and can’t let the kid hold you back from getting your kombucha fix.

name: Andrew Roberts
text:
Where to start? Such a great spot to have drink. The kombucha is not very acidic or super sweet like I was expecting from experiences at other places. They have a menu with a good amount of tasting options and believe me when I say they all taste REALLY good. The Strawberry Mojito was excellent, I definitely recommend starting there if its your first time with kombucha.
Local Roots looks and smells like its brand new, and from my opinion they have made the space into a very nice place to come after work and enjoy some downtime. They have Jenga and Cornhole for entertainment as well as a couple TVs and plenty of seating space.
Definitely a spot I will be visiting again soon and I would recommend this place as a must visit spot.

resp.text: Thanks for the great review Andrew! We hope to see you again soon! We’re always working to get better so let us know if there’s anything we can do to improve.

resp.text: We apologize for the security raising his voice, that is something we don't tolerate, but we have had guests with issues hearing people through the masks.  We will speak to him about this to make sure he's using a more professional tone.  This is a curbside location, so we do ask that you stay in your car due to the COVID laws to keep you and our employees safe.  You are more an welcome to place your order on site with your budtender, but if the order is already placed online, they must verify the ID before bringing any items out due to CA state laws.  If you'd prefer a walk in shop, we have several in the area, though it may take longer than our curbside pick up.  We hope you continue to be a customer with Haven, whether it's through our Express location or another.  Have a wonderful night. ❤

name: Brandon Gibbs
text:
Students and staff of UCLA avoid university housing at all costs! It's run by crooks, thieves, and terrible people. They give zero care about human life or safety. Elevators get stuck and have issues non stop, and are FIVE YEARS PAST THEIR INSPECTION DATE. If you're in a wheelchair prepare to just not have access to your home at times. The repairs are slow and sloppy. Air condition units out for weeks on end (not unit, UNITS, because they have unsafe and outdated power delivery to the building, which blew out many residents units at once, in the winter.... Not even under heavy load), with zero ETA for fixes..... Why? Because they use student labor as a front for everything! Any complaint you make, any request you have, goes to an underpaid student, that gets no support for UCLA itself. The owners should be arrested or at the very least banned from building ownership ever again. This is unforgivable and I have no idea how they sleep at night, gouging students and staff day after day and can't even do BASIC ROUTINE MAINTENANCE.

Oh and the stairs are broken for months. No eta for that.

Rusted and broken railing laying on the ground for years.... No eta to fix that.

Pool that is never cleaned. After a year of waiting and finally asking we were told it "should be cleaned daily". Now it seems like it gets at least bi-annual cleaning.

Gym room with broken equipment. The room was redone too a couple years ago, but the broken machines were left in place.

Car garage that has many thefts every year from poor security, including thefts of locked bikes.

The list would go on but I've only so much time. These crooks need to be punished, and I feel so bad for all the students and staff that keep having to put up with this.

But no, I got skipped and there I go waiting again. He said that the guy next to him was going to take care of my haircut, but honestly at this point i'm impatient. text:
I've found my dentistry!  NOT. I've been through the gamut of dentists over the years but this is "the one".  After being ripped off with leaking, failing root canals and 1000's of dollars spent at other dentistry's I'm quite sure San Marcos Smile Dentistry is my dentistry.  NOT!!  Since joining, I've had two teeth pulled, bridge work done, a root canal and a teeth cleaning and I am totally pleased with the results...OR SO I THOUGHT.... My, how first impressions change!  I
wiIl l NEVER return to this hack artist dentistry!  After my final visit I noticed two teeth that had holes drilled through the enamel between the teeth.. One of those teeth have now rotted off and the other is decaying.  I lost my dental insurance and don't have the money to get it repaired.  My tongue felt the holes right away although I never got around to going back.  Now my front tooth next to the canine is rotting and 75% gone..... It's almost like they purposely damaged my good teeth to drum up more business.  I will never go back there unless its for a pro bono tooth repair job to fix the damage they caused!

name: Jeka Lambert
text:
I went online to apply at River City Staffing.  The website wanted candidates to upload their resume.  I called River City Staffing to find out if they were looking for a resume that they would use to screen me, or if they were looking for a resume that could be forwarded to employers.  The recruiter told me they were looking for a resume that contained my work history.  I got the recruiter's name and email address.

I sent her a cover letter explaining that I'd been out of the corporate world for a number of years and I attached a paragraph style resume that highlighted my office skills, had my most pertinent info on the first page and my work history on the second page.

The recruiter replied via email that she hadn't read my resume because it was "unclear" and she was "confused" by the paragraph style.  She told me we could discuss employment opportunities only after I rewrote my resume to conform to a bullet style template which she sent as an attachment.

I called the recruiter because I wasn't sure how to make my resume conform to the template.  The recruiter was very condescending when she explained that a resume "must" be bulleted and in chronological order.  I responded that my most pertinent work experience was not my most recent employment, and that I'd written my resume in a way that emphasized my most pertinent experience, but I did include my work history so she had a sense of the kinds of work I've done.   The recruiter insisted that I use her template.  I said I didn't think we'd be a good fit.

In the mean time, I landed a job with another agency using the resume rejected by River City Staffing.  When I asked the other recruiter if he would like me to revise my resume, he said my resume was fine.  (This conversation occurred before the exchange with RCS.)

Walk-in access comes from Cherry Valley Boulevard near the water tank, and through several walking Gates on Beaumont Avenue. This area is adjacent to a city park where they play soccer which is to the South, on Beaumont Avenue. The safety of the residents and their belongings are not of any concern to the owner of this place. Months now have passed and a few weeks back I was told corporate cleared a check to fix the stair, but it's still broken 5 months down the road.

Miller insurance a provider of rental insurance started by family of CEO of PLP Jeff Miller are incauhuts bambosaling tenats for as much money as they can stuff in their hollow hearts.

text: I went to TLC Chiropractic for hip pain. I have had the pain constantly for about 2 years and It was affecting my work and my ability to exercise. At my first appointment with Dr.Caruthers he took the time to listen to me and talked me through what he thought would help and how he would do it. Before using Dr.Caruthers I had had a previous chiropractor who hurt my neck and I was, frankly, scared and soured on chiropractic care. I told Dr.Caruthers about my previous experience and he made me feel comfortable and explained what he was going to do physically before doing it.  He was professional and capable. I have a better range of movement in my hip now and the pain has much improved.

name: stacey kearns
text:
Dr. Caruthers is an amazing Chiropractor and knows his field very well. I have gone to him for 5 different injuries. I have had back injuries from work and a few bad rear end car accidents.  Everytime I have gone to him I had an incredible experience and started to recover and get pain relief quickly from his professional services.  I had a very irregular schedule and he allowed me to come in at different times since it was hard for me to schedule an exact time every visit. His ability to work with my schedule was a huge plus and I was always seen quickly and he always answered any questions I had. Dr. Timothy Caruthers has also helped me with other helpful health information that not only makes sense but has helped me be strong and sickness free for the last 25 years of my life. I'm now 52 years old and can out perform guys at my work that are 20 years younger then me, with his advice and services I feel great all the time and have stayed fit and healthy.  Thank you so much Tim for your truly amazing skills and knowledge of the entire human body, because of you I feel great all the time.
I have had such great recovery after my accidents that I will always return to Dr. Caruthers if I ever injured again.
Thank you,
Stacey  Kearns

resp.text: Wow. Thanks for the phenomenal review Stacey. It was very humbling. Thank you!

name: Ally Edwards
text: So yeah, I feel ahhhhhmazing! Clean establishment, friendly Doc., timely, and knowledgeable. And as a first time chiropractic patient, all of this was important to me to keep my nerves calm lol. He only cracked my focus area (I only had one), and I’m legit now moving in ways to “search” for that pain that was previously there, and can EVER SO SLIGHTLY feel where it may have been... but it’s totally not even worth mentioning or complaining about anymore. So it might by psychological 😅 🤷🏽‍♀️, but those issues are for another doctor lmao. But omg, I’m sold!!! I’ve been living with uncomfortable tightness in my lower back for MONTHSSSSSSS now, and not to feel it anymore makes me so happy 🙌🏾. I didn’t know what to expect initially, and thought I was going to get a full body adjustment. But I was informed that you only treat the problematic areas, otherwise you’ll develop issues that didn’t exist before. I definitely appreciated the helpful piece of information because I’m sure most newbies thought what I did. But thank you again!!!  I’ll definitely keep this apart of my self care routine, and will see you soon!

text: Variety of sandals have really gone down hill, sandals are old fashion and nothing was close to being wearable. They use to have a great selection of cute vionic sandals that i would buy several pairs at a time. Now I couldnt find even a regular black pair. Also I bought a brace that would help with my plantar fasciitis and when I put it on to ease some pain it didn't fit right and caused pain in other areas, couldnt wear it for even 2 minutes 💔 and i called and was told I couldn't return it. What a waste of time and alot of money.

resp.text:
Kristy,

We are disappointed that you felt the need to leave us a one star review. Please let us address both of your issues:

In regards to our “variety of sandals hav[ing] gone downhill,” please consider the following:
a)	We, as a society, are now three months into the crippling COVID-19 pandemic.
b)	This pandemic first hit China, where nearly all of the footwear (including the sandals you buy) is manufactured.
c)	As such, supply chains were cut off for months.
d)	In addition, most footwear stores were deemed “non-essential” and closed for 2 months or longer.
e)	In response, our supplier slashed retail prices to call it quits on their summer line (right as spring started), and we responded by doing the same.
f)	Being that we were one of the only stores that carry the product that was allowed to open our doors, our product has been picked over, with no incentive from the supplier to replenish inventory at cut-rate margins.
g)	Vionic, in particular, has moved away from large varieties of sandals, and has focused their growth on their more fashion-forward products, including boots and dress shoes.
h)	We cannot stock more than what Vionic manufactures.
i)	This portion of your review can be summarily dismissed, as it is very much a reflection of the current state of the world and the manufacturing choices of our supplier.

In regards to the brace that you were unable to return, please consider the following:
a)	You purchased the brace yesterday at 1:01PM and called to inquire about returning it at 2:46PM.
b)	The item you purchased is meant for overnight use while sleeping.
c)	It is not uncommon for any new brace or orthopedic device to cause discomfort when first being used, as you and your body acclimate to the product.
d)	We clearly indicate that, for health and hygiene purposes (which are heighted amid the COVID-19 pandemic), all products at this time are non-returnable.
e)	Additionally, we will not take immediate returns on any item meant to be used overnight, and before any period of acclimation has been allowed.
f)	However, we are very much willing to work with any and all customers to help in fitting, application, etc.
g)	This portion of your review can also be dismissed by the simple fact that you wrote it within hours of purchasing an item that is supposed to be worn overnight, and can take several days to acclimate to.

We hope to be able to continue to help you as you endeavor to relieve your foot pain. It is our mission to help improve the way you Walk, Move, Sit and Sleep.

text:
Poor service. Unfortunately my auto insurance contracts with Gil's so I did not have an option. Made the call for a tow at 9:30am through my insurance. Received a text 30 minutes later from Gil's, no ETA. Tried calling Gil's by phone, phone rang and rang, no answer, no voicemail option. On the 4th try, got though. Was assured someone would be there in 45 minutes. After an hour and a half, the driver told my insurance he was at my location, which he wasn't. Finally, 10 minutes later, he showed up, more than 2 hours after service call. He apologized for the delay, and expressed surprise that his boss did not dispatch another available driver. He stated there were other drivers, but he did not start work until 11am.

I can understand delays - as long as they are justified. But the dishonest reporting to my insurance and the extended delay shows neglect and unethical business practices.

There are other tow companies in the area. One stopped by my location asking if I needed assistance and offered me some bottled water. I wish my insurance contracted with them instead.

text: All the teachers have been great with my 7 year old son who just started swim lessons for the first time a month ago. His first teacher had a schedule change due to school, then we had a substitute for one day, then we switched to a different day/time with his current teacher. They were all good with children (patient, nice, funny) and did basically the same routines as each other during the 30 minute lesson (so there's consistency even if it's a different teacher). I like how they get the kids to go just a tiny bit past what they thought they could do, without forcing or scaring them. They just think they're having fun and playing games. name: adam pham
text: So I sold my sports car to buy a commuter, I know very mature adult thing to do. I did it for my growing family. Anyways, I didn't want to spend too much on this vehicle since it's not very important to me other than to be reliable and safe.  To make it alittle more comfortable for my kids and myself, I wanted to tint the windows for a good price. Don't get me wrong, the expensive ones do a great job. When I contacted Boris and we talked about what I wanted and got a price qoute, I was shocked. Sometimes you get a price too good to be true, WELL in this case it's true. I was expecting a guy doing window tinting in his home or run down place. Boris is actually very skilled and very focused. He did 9 windows total in roughly 2hrs with small talks and breaks. I respect him and love to do business with hard working skilled people. He's honest and hard working. No BS and gets all of the business because of his very very very affordable price. I'm actually glad I found him and I will continue to do business with him as long as he's still tinting. The brand he uses seems to be reputable and not generic. I did alittle research on it while I was waiting. He also does higher end products like ceramic tints( Suntek and 3M) it rejects heat alot better. I will be referring him to my friends and family from now on.

text: I gave this botanical a 1 star because the "healer" man that owns/runs the place is a fraud. I initially stopped by to buy candles. Once inside, I was about to make my purchase and found out the did readings ( he called it " consultas". The price for a reading was reasonable. I think it was $35. So I accepted. We went into his little office, he asked me for my first and last name and date of birth. He didn't ask me if I had a specific question or why was I there. He laid out my cards and then gave me my reading. After about a 10 minute reading he gave me some concerning feedback and said I needed to be cleansed of all the negativity. He didn't explain what each card meant he just gave me his interpretation of things and it was serious matters. He said his cleansing would cost $390 for 10 minutes. RIP OFF!! I ended up going to House of Intuition a few days later to get a second reading and spiritual healing. I paid $90 for 1 hour of tarot reading and shamanic healing. The tarot cards revealed the same information however the interpretation was completely different. I got my chakras aligned and found out that I have a calling of healer. The botanical guy had distorted the interpretation of my cards so that he could dwindle me out of $400!! All I can say is that karma will return to him x3. Stop in for candles or sage but do not get readings from this man. Go to House of Intuition for readings.

Unfortunately, this driving school offer very expensive behind ther wheel driving lessons ($320/2hr) while competition charges between $80 to $140/2hr driving lessons.  Furthermore, the driving instructor failed to instruct the student (my daughter) properly. On top of this the instructor had the student stop at the gas station to fill up the empty gas tank.

Also, the person handling the phone answering service needs to learn to be much more polite.

Overall, this driving school is quite expensive,  driving instructor is not teaching well and the secretary answering the phone is rude.  Your money is better spent elsewhere

resp.text:
It is evident that this review has been written by our competitors around the corner from us. We charge $100 for two hours of behind the wheel lessons and $279 for six hours. I don't think any school in San Diego charges this insane amount you wrote. We never make our students put gas in our vehicles, this is unacceptable and has never happened in our 20+ years of business.

We take great pride in our reputation and our customer service. Please kindly reach out to me with a student's name if I am wrong about this being a competitor trying to bring a hard working family owned business down. we understand times are rough, but this is not a kind thing to do. We can all win together in this economy.

name: Guadalupe Ruiz
text:
DISGUSTED! 0/10 CUSTOMER SERVICE

My mom went in to look for a wheelchair to donate and she had gone in before and was priced at $45. Today she went in to purchase and she was priced $75! There was a second wheelchair in better condition so she asked about that one and was priced $85. The lady told my mom that she didn't care what they had told her the past days, the wheelchair was $75. After I got there the lady didn't speak to me, she just looked me up and down. While my mom and I were talking trying to figure out if this is the wheelchair we wanted to purchase I kept feeling uneasy because she kept passing by us but not really with a purpose. We decided to purchase and got in line, still talking about how happy the lady we were donating it to would be. I was skeptic on the price as we went in with an idea and was priced different but whatever, sometimes co-workers get prices wrong. We decided we were gonna talk with the cashier and ask if that price was the least, we weren't too hopeful as the lady had already rudely told us the price was $85, "because the cushion alone is $180". We didn't care too much for the cushion, but we figured it was nice discount and slightly worn.

Everything was going semi-good when she came around the building and yelled, from the door, (!!!YELLED!!!) at the cashier, that the wheelchair is $85. He wasn't even finished with his current customer yet. My mother is kind and hates conflict, bless her soul. But this lady's tone of voice when directed at us or about us was rude and as if she felt we were stealing or something. She yelled it loud as if to let everyone know we were there, buying a wheelchair???
I don't want to point to racism here, I've had very few encounters with racism as I am Mexican but speak perfect English. But there's no other way to explain the tone of voice she used at us. The looks she gave us, or that she yelled at the cashier as if to say "I'm sure they will try to haggle but that item is $85 so I'm gonna tell so everyone is aware".

Now I love this store, don't get me wrong sometimes they have beautiful items. But this lady made me have a sour taste whenever I think of this store now. Very very disappointed. We took our business elsewhere and found what we were looking for. 👎

name: Timothy Spano
text:
The Sunglass Hut on 2nd street great if you're looking to spend over $150 on sunglasses that were made in China, get scratched easily, and won't last you over a year.

I've purchased a total of 3 sunglasses here, one pair which ended up getting extremely uncomfortable (I ended up losing these), one pair which I returned, and my current pair which already need lens replacements after 1 month of wearing. The glasses all look very nice, however they have the quality and lifespan of $20 pharmacy sunglasses. The lenses are mostly plastic, and every pair is made in China.

The reason I give this place 2 stars rather than 3, is because I was sold a pair of sunglasses from a salesman of theirs who ensured me that I was getting sunglasses with GLASS lenses. I need glass lenses because otherwise they'll get scratched. However, after purchasing and using them for a week, I realized that the lenses were in fact still plastic, despite what the salesman told me. I tried to return the glasses, but they refused to exchange them.

Overall a nice place if you don't mind dropping a few hundred dollars on glasses you can find in a pharmacy.

#ProTip -- Bring cash to pay for it, and you don't have to pay extra! (Card is extra.)
#ProTip --- Call in advance to see if they have something you need! I did this several times when I needed a new laptop charger and they were able to tell me if they were in stock! Then I just went over and picked it up.
#ProTip --- Ask them for helpful tips for saving memory on your computer, or ask them for advice for keeping your laptop/device happy and healthy in the long run! Take advantage of their tech knowledge! :)

I'm sure there's more #ProTips out there for these guys but one thing - they've been there for me all this time and I am sooo thankful for their service.

God bless you <3.

-Alexandra C.

name: Randy Chalenor
text:
I've received and given more foot massages then I can remember from the West Coast to the East coast (in the US) also in Thailand.  AND I was thrilled to have a massage at Ankang Massage and Reflexology the other day.
Being in the middle of the Covid Pandemic it was very hard to find a Asian Foot massage studio open. Everything was as it should be when I arrived: Clean, organized lobby and group foot massage area. I arrived with 2 friends and they placed us with social distancing in mind (I had a barrier between me the next client.) We all wore masks throughout  the procedure and also a towel draped over our faces for added protection (a nice touch.)  My masseuse (LeeLee) was excellent!  Thorough and gifted in giving me my massage she brought pressure up to the pain threshold and then backed down several times in tense tight spots. By the time she was done I was totally relaxed without feeling beat up.  Verbal communication was a little broken but There was little I need to communicate because of the skill of the masseuse.

I will be back even though they are across town.

After a very hard work week I needed some relief for my sore muscles so stopped in at Jun Jun for a foot massage. Not the typical foot massage I've received; no foot soak or pressure point massage of the forehead. Not a lot of work on my arms or hands however what she did worked I left a lot less sore and stiff. The masseuses process was quite intense much of the time but like I said it worked. Often when a masseuse goes in deep before relaxing the muscles you leave feeling beat up. text:
"I'm just so excited to smog my car," said no one ever. It's not so bad, however, if you give Full Service Automotive a shot. Normally I'd go to a local spot and get it over with, but the Groupon deal I found for them was too good to pass up.

I came early on a Saturday morning and was initially disappointed to hear that their technician had not arrived for the day yet. One of the workers (perhaps the owner?) promptly called to see where the tech was. He gave me a quick update and even bought me a drink from shop's convenience store. His friendly demeanor and attentiveness helped turn things around. The tech arrived within 20 minutes and my car was taken care of within 10 minutes. Surprisingly, the smog check was completed a lot quicker than other shops I've been to. One big reason for that is this place does not put the car on rollers and through acceleration tests.

I came for the good deal, but also left with great service and a passing mark for my car.

Very friendly and really REALLY great about following up with us so to keep the process moving along. To show their appreciation, they sent us cookies! Kevin also reached out to help us refinance 6 months later for a lower rate. I would highly recommend Greenhaven Capital.

resp.text: Thanks for your review!  We really appreciate your business.  It was great working with you!

text: Kevin Oto was a pleasure to work with. Highly recommended.

name: John Campos
text: Kevin, Kyle, and the whole Team at Greenhaven Capital are professional, incredibly responsive, and do everything the full service, no short cuts, late night conversation, work until the job is done, roll the sleeves up, never quit, never faulter, top notch service at a interest rate and no or low fees cost below any competitor. I have been in this business for 10+ years and my best transactions have been with this team. There are issues in any home, loan, or escrow but this team is who I want on my side to push past the objections life throws our way. They have the experience, the lender relationships, and the underwriting skill to carry myself and my clients successfully to the finish line time and time again. It has always been a joy to work with the team. Their no nonsense attitude comes across in every step of the way and their team thrives in a constant communication environment like todays market. I am at a minimum receiving updates about our buyers files several times a week and most times it's accompanied with a call and or text. Kevin is a true professional, and he runs a tight ship full of similar professionals. I highly Recommend him and anyone on his team.

name: Jonathan Fong
text:
Kevin Oto and the Green Haven Capital staff provided superior customer service. I was looking to refinance my home and after the headache of dealing with online quotes I decided to call Green Haven Capital. Before I called Kevin, I had received a quote from another broker and wanted to see if he could match rates. Not only was he able to match the rate, but he was able to save me money in closing fee's.

If I ever had a question Kevin promptly answered by phone, e-mail, or text. Kevin even took the time to answer my questions after office hours.  Would highly recommend for first time buyers or families seeking re-financing options.

name: A B
text: Kevin Oto’s patience, knowledge and diligence made our VA loan approval simple.  We had a particular hurdle to overcome with VA and Kevin managed it beyond expectations. He was always available and responded with answers in minimal time. We are referring him to 2 of our family members who are beginning the home purchasing process. Thanks Kevin!

name: Ted Brick
text: There was a time Moss Motors was a great vendor in the past. It has changed and gone bad to do any business with. I have been a customer for years and was able to get parts for my MG MGB British roadster. Recently 2018, their customer service and ordering  of parts has become a real hassle. Common parts on sale are out of stock - back ordered with no idea when they will be available ("couple of weeks"}.  They now have a parts catalogue of cheaply made parts and a lot of back order- out of stock. The shipping cost are very expensive too and slow to deliver. Most of the Moss phone customer service people are now uninformed and very very rude. I would not recommend anyone to do business with Moss Motors.

name: Michelle Rowe
text:
I will start this by stating that before I came here, I have never had Ramen before.

I love the Inner Sunset and all the fun little restaurants that are scattered around 9th and Irving. This gem is off 9th between Irving and Lincoln. With so many options in the area I feel as if this place can get overlooked. I was definitely wrong because this place was packed! The decor is welcoming and the staff is extremely efficient. I ordered the Ramen and was pleasantly surprised. It was really tasty! I felt that nothing in the bowl overpowered the other flavors, yet instead it was a wonderful harmonious blend of delicious! I can't wait to come back and try more dishes!

text: This was an awesome spot right at the Giants Ballpark! Awesome quick bites and all Mexican Style. However, they are no longer at this location. There is one close by at the Ferry Building. It's a nice walk along the Embarcadero and walk in the Ferry Building and you'll see it.

name: Michelle Rowe
text:
I think I found the best Mexican-style nachos in the city!
So this place has three great things:
1. Nachos done right with melted cheese, not a cheese sauce.
2. They put a tortilla on the bottom of the plate so anything you don't get on a chip now becomes part of an encore burrito.
3. They have carnitas!
The portion size is perfect for two people to share. I really liked their guacamole too. Everything was spot on with these nachos.
I recommend coming here before a Giants game to grab a bite to eat and then go next door to the public house (they are literally joined so you don't have to go outside) and grab two reasonably priced beers which you can take into the ballpark with you!

Frank was incredibly nice and welcoming, asked me my name and was very friendly. Unfortunately he seemed more concerned with what he wanted then what I did. I told him I was just starting off getting into the hobby of drying and displaying leaves and wanted advice on how to do so myself, I had only come to buy a glass riser, an accessory I heard would help preserve my leaves, costing about $20 bucks online.
His response was to leave it to the professionals or it'd look 'copy and pasted' and proceeded to let me know he could do it for me starting at $200 and upwards of $400 depending on glass, frames etc
He seemed very knowledgable and I'm sure if you're looking for professional framing he'd be a great help, but I left feeling very disheartened to start my new hobby.

To continue providing this essential service while providing a safer service operation for our customers and colleagues, we have temporarily adjusted the operations for our branches across the country. All current hours are listed on our website at: usbank.com/locations and we are keeping that page up-to-date as changes occur. In the meantime, many transactions can be completed 24 hours a day at usbank.com, using the U.S. Bank Mobile App, using a U.S. Bank ATM or by calling our 24-Hour Customer Service at 800-872-2657. After prepping my nails, that's when they asked me about color. The one doing my hands cut me a little while doing my cuties, only put 2 coats of a "glitter shade" with no solid color underneath to make the glitter pop. By the time he finished my nails he told me to sit by the drying station I noticed that my nails where bubbling so I talked to the receptionist and she said to talk to "him". He came And pretend to act surprise. He said he would fix but that i would have to wait. So 3 min later he takes some acetone and rubbs the clear coat off with his finger. He proceeds to apply a thicker cost of polish plus clear coat and walks me to drying station as to make sure I didn't do whatever I did to cause the nail polish to bubble. So as my nails are drying they start to bubble AGAIN I inform him and he comes and looks at my nails and pretends that only one has bubbles so I correct him and tell him that no that all of them are bubbling. Again he tells me that I have to wait for 5 min so this time he roughly unpolished my nails and actually took his time and polished my nail correctly. By the time my nails dried I was happy finally no bubbles!  Here comes the real shocker I went on Saturday so on Monday I am looking over my bank account and noticed that I have a  charge of $109.00 from Phantastic Nails!  So I went to nail shop asking to speak to a manager or person in charge I was told to take a seat and wait for 10 min. I told her that I was not going to wait for 10 min that if there was someone in charge or not. She stopped what she was doing and asked what the problem was. I told her of the charge and she said that it was a mistake that the guy had charge my account by mistake........ So I lost my cool and got a bit loud. She said plead wait let me get my manager on the phone. She called some one and spoke in her native tongue then handed me the phone. So this lady said it was a mistake and that they refunded my money back I told her that one as not seeing any refund and that if it was a mistake why was I not informed. Again I was told to wait that she was going to call the guy in charge of their credit card machine. So this guy starts telling me that the refund was issued to give it 3 days and I would see the refund. If not to call him and that " we could work something out". So I'm so done by this point I tell him that I will be contacting my bank to inform of the fraudulent charge. He said that I could do that but that they had paper work and that they would re charge my credit card. So I asked what paperwork you have no signature on receipt for 109.00 dollar charge. I never authorized that charge. We be talking to my bank tomorrow as it was closed by the time I left nail shop.

name: Leann Jaramillo
text: We decided to go with Ram Jack when our foundation was in need of restoration.   Initially speaking with and having a consult with Kyle, the GM, who took the time to explain everything that needed to be done and put our minds at ease because this was going to be a big job.   They started work Monday morning early, the team outside, with preparation for the installation of the helical piles.  They worked fast and efficiently.  When Tuesday came around they started working on the inside fixes.  By Wednesday afternoon they had finished both shoring up the house  on the outside and grinding/ repairing all the cracks on the inside.   The whole team was competent and efficient.  Special shout out to Andrew the site manager,  and Jack the grinder and Crack repair guy.   Both were obviously good at their jobs and made us feel like we could trust them with our home.   We are happy with this service and although we hope never to have any more foundation problems,  we would recommend them to anyone.  True professionals.

name: J B
text:
We were experiencing a few settling issues in our new to us 1950's house and the home inspector originally told us we should get the foundation inspected further as there was significant water in the crawlspace.

We knew there were some drainage issues that we have been addressing for the last few months so we figured better call an expert to look at the foundation and tell us what needs to be fixed. We were also concerned about some off center posts and small cracks in the concrete the home inspector showed us.

We scheduled an appointment and Kyle showed up right on time. He explained the process and said he'd need about an hour to take some measurements, use a level to see if there was any sinking, and to go underneath the house to check the crawlspace. He mentioned that he'd provide an honest assessment when he was done.

To our astonishment, once Kyle was done, he said there were no real concerns to note, so our house was provided a clean bill of foundation health! He even explained how the terrain we live on has helped keep the house very level since it's not on a clay bed.

Kyle was true to his word. Class act that is harder to find these days. I highly recommend them, not just because we didn't have to pay anything, but because they are honest!

name: joey horvitz
text: Said they couldn't help. Seemed like they didn't want to go through the effort. Not sure exactly why. It is an old house. Perhaps they only touch modern standard foundations. They suggested other companies. I wonder why they're not able to perform the same work of the other companies they recommended? Ah well.

resp.text:
Hey Joey,

Ram Jack Pacific specializes in Foundation Repair and stabilization, on occasion if services outside our primary expertise are needed we will recommend one of our trusted industry partners.

Regardless, it sounds like your experience left some questions unanswered. A manager will give you a call today to see if we can be of any further assistance and offer greater clarity on why we recommended an industry partner.

Ram Jack Pacific prides itself on customer service and our Foundation Specialists are trained to provide honest and transparent evaluations. We'll never try and sell a service we don't perform or that a customer does not need.

Thank you for feedback Joey, we will reach out later today.

Sincerely,

The Ram Jack Pacific Team

name: Maya P.
text: Being a fellow artist myself, I can recognize excellence when I see it....and well, this was it! Swan is the best, no contest :) I finally got to lay in the procedure chair and become the client to get my brows designed by Swan. And what a treat. He made me feel very comfortable and made it a collaborative process in which what he drew on was exactly what I got... In a nutshell, Swan is very professional, hygienic with equipment and process, attentive to detail, and incredibly talented, and so nice.  It was a joy to see the glee and excitement permeating from his eyes as he perfected my brows. You can clearly see he takes pride in his work and demands nothing short of superb work from himself...After my brows were done, I was surprised - they didn't even feel like they were just tattooed. My face felt the same as it did before the procedure. It was not painful with the cocktail of wonderful numbing agents used...If you need brow work done and want nothing short of excellence,  then you've found it with Swan.Perfection and Impressive is all I can say... I am a very happy client. A+

name: Jeff & Renee Ranallo
text:
I was really impressed by Swan and his talent. However, when we were chit-chatting while he was marking my brows the subject of God came up and he asked if I believed God was a healer. I responded that I was an atheist and his whole demeanor changed. All of a sudden he was going to have his scheduler be in touch (he didn't mention a scheduler when I scheduled this appt). I said, "Wait, aren't you going to tattoo me today?" He said on the phone that this appointment would be 3 hours and even said early in the appointment that after today about 50% of the color would peel off so I fully believe the intent was to tattoo me today. He now said that this was a consultation and that I should get a couple more consults - "in fact, I highly recommend that you check out at least 2 others and see how you feel about them". He was giving me the bum's rush even though there was nobody else there. He even walked out and walked over to another part of the salon before I was done calling my ride. He did come back to ask if I wanted a water while I wait for my ride.

I was really disappointed with the whole situation as he CLEARLY no longer wanted to do my brows because of my religious beliefs. I believe he has every right to choose his customers however he wishes, but my religion or lack thereof has nothing to do with how good of a customer I am. I think I'll take his suggestion and get another consult - and give my money to them.

resp.text: Renee thank you for coming in today for your consultation, which is absolutley necessary before moving forward with any Permanent make-up treatments. After the first consult, we then will schedule the procedure date as I told you today. THIS IS OUR POLICY WITH NO EXCEPTIONS.! I did mention that the Eyebrow treatment does take 3+ hrs to complete  After consultation has been conducted and both client and technician agreed upon all aspects of the service in question, Furthermore  Religion, belief's or politics ect.. is not a basis of not rendering a service to anyone for any reason. It's just no so, I'm saddened by this please forgive me if you feel this way. However Your consultation was completely complimentary we waived the $50.00 fee, we hope we helped by giving you educated information on the whole process of Eyebrow tattooing I even Drew your eyebrows on for you to wear for the day before having them permanently tattoo'd. As I agreed with you, you said (it is your face) I did recommend as I always do to every client to get at least 2 other consultation, Before doing any permanent tattooing. We only want what's best for anyone wanting to have permanent procedure's done, I do wish you the very best in your  eyebrow journey.

Since it came with an alarm and had no way to set the alarm.. so I changed my review from 4/5 to 1/5.. also that navy fed check you get for a car can also be used as a down payment for many other cars remember that.. you always have a choice in everything.. plus they like to call and see how much you qualify with Navy Fed and then tell you the car choices you can get based off that check and the actual car you want that they advertised and then most dealerships pay for your fees here they charge you when it comes in cause they don’t send the plates to your address.. Overall wouldn’t recommend anyone come here.. never have..

name: Danté Vincent
text:
I recently bought an authentic newspaper from WW2 announcing the end of the war, and wanted to have it framed and preserved as much as possible as it's truly a piece of history. After doing some research I knew Allan Jeffries was the best option based on user reviews and I was not disappointed.

Fortuitously, when I first stopped in to discuss having my item framed, it was Allan himself who helped me. He explained that he too used to have quite a collection of old / vintage newspapers and other historical items so I immediately knew I came to the right place. Allan was incredibly helpful and knowledgeable and even provided a discount for the work. I was so pleased with the experience I brought in a few more posters and items to have framed by them.

PRO TIP: mention the deal on Yelp. Some of the employees won't immediately offer (or even know about it), so be sure to mention it.

I'm beyond happy with the quality of the work.
I'm also glad to see they are taking every precaution necessary to make sure the employees and customers are safe. Everyone needs to wear a mask, they provide gloves, hand sanitizers, limit the number of customers in the store at any given time, etc. They are now even doing contact tracing.

A+ for your incredible service, Allan & team. Keep up the amazing work.

name: Chef Bernie Guzman

Dan knows his stuff when it comes to Toyota/Lexus. I learned so much about the needs of my truck, how it functions and I could help it run better and last longer. Dan is not just a mechanic, he is also a teacher. He doesn’t just care about getting something fixed quickly, he cares about the details and getting it done right, with the right parts and ensuring that you understand what’s being done and why. Also, in the end he saved me money, but the best part is that my truck has never run better and I’ve never been more comfortable or confident in its performance.

Dan even recommended me what kind of tires to buy. Dan is  full of knowledge and takes a lot of pride in the work he does. He is a great mechanic but a even  better person. I'm definitely coming back to his shop to get service on my Toyota.

resp.text: Thank you Jose for your business and your time to leave a great review! Your Camry is very new with only 35,000 miles and brake rotors vibrations are usually caused by over torqued wheel lug nuts during tires rotation. I felt bad that it happened to your vehicle and it’s an annoying problem that has to be fixed ASAP for your safety. Front rotors measured at .004 of an inch run out and the rear had .003 of an inch warpage. The max specifications for any brake rotors are .001, or lower to give you the maximum braking force, performance and a smooth driving experience on the new vehicle’s braking system. Factory service has always delivered best result for your Toyota to the fullest! And thank you Jose for the recommendations!

I just picked up a Mercedes,it needed new break pads rotors and sensors so I started calling places and getting quotes,I read all foreign autos reviews and decided to give them a try since the MB dealership was quoting me over $1000 for everthing parts and labor.i called them and spoke to Jose, and he gave me a quote that noone else I called could beat.the next Friday I scheduled an  appointment to do the break job.i asked if they offered shuttle service (since I work like half a mile from their location) and Jose gladly offered it. dropped off my Mercedes around 1030am.shuttle took me back to work and picked me up when I got off at 3pm.got back to my car, paid and left effortlessly. they did a great job to my breaks while providing great customer service.
I have since returned for more maintenence on my car and every time they deliever.A+ for Jose and his skilled workers.my new spot for my mercedes.

name: Carlos Camargo
text:
John the Tailor Man is a great tailor with 55 years of experience.  He is a master of his craft, and stays abreast of current trends.  I was in a serious bind and needed a badly bungled alteration to a suit fixed by noon the next day.  He assured me he would fix it and he did.  He's professional, courteous, and friendly.  I will definitely bring my alteration needs to him rather than take a chance with the sometimes questionable work of in-house tailors and seamstresses at the suit outlets.  He charged me so little for this great, rushed job that I was embarrassed and now feel I under tipped.  Don't take my word for it, go see John.  You'll know when discussing your request that he's the man for the job.
He can make custom clothing too, and matching tie with suspenders for when you absolutely, positively gotta look sharp.

name: Stefano Brenna
text:
Given the cost of the rent and the quality of service that is offered I strongly do not recommend this community.

I lived here for around a year with my fiancee and I only recently relocated. I was initially attracted by two things . The first was the Move-In special that seemed convenient given the medium-high price of the apartments and the second one was the vicinity of the freeway. However my move in was in a rush because I was visiting family in Europe and also switching between two jobs from SD to OC.   I didn't consider enough elements before making my decision.

A. URBAN AREA : Too close to the freeway and the train: from several spots of the building or from my apartment with the window open you could hear the background noise and when the train passes part of the building shakes.

B. NEIGHBORHOOD isn't awesome. I've seen various times homeless people being reckless and police stopping them. Walking around isn't great as it's just a big intersection between crown-vallwy, the train and the freeway. You don't really wanna walk to any malls from there. Sometimes strangers/ non residents try to get into the complex using various excuses. It didn't feel very safe. For a while there has been open a very loud bar in front of it , I  witnessed resident who were trying to sleep at night shouting at the bar customers and starting "fights". Now that bar is closed.

C. NIGHT TIME: Several times during the year the fire alarm (so loud) started ringing in the middle of the night and everyone had to go in the street. One night it happened twice. Management said it was sometimes because of tenants burning food in the oven, sometimes smoking , or sometimes just a malfunction. Fire brigades came all the times and all the times management said that was not going to happen again. It happened several times so who knows...
It also happened around 5 times , days and nights, that some neighbor rang our doorbell and ran. Whether it was a prank or a mistake the doorbells are so loud that you'd wake up if you are sleeping. So annoying.

D.  AMENITIES: are good and new, but the complex is big and they can get crowded, especially on weekends.

E: SERVICE and PARKING: management is quick making repairs and very quick to charge you as well. In general they have always been responsive.

Parking is somewhat ok.They once double assigned one of my paid parking spots to another tenant and had me park in the guest space for few weeks. Many other residents just consistently park in the guest spaces, every night I suppose without paying. I never witnessed actions to enforce the rules, but a few emails.

My impression is that they try to fix problems but the community is very big and many residents seemed to not respect the rules and thus it looks like the management is always running after something or someone.

F. DEPOSIT: We left the apartment clean, as clean as I found it. Normal wear and tear barely noticeable or unnoticeable. I spent an afternoon cleaning and they still charged us for the whole deposit amount.

Not a tragic experience all in all but definitely not very pleasant. I have lived in better places with lower rent.

resp.text: Stefano, we regret to hear that your experience with us was not a more positive one. We will take your feedback and use it to improve our services in the future. Thank you for taking the time to provide your feedback to us!

name: Ted Fletcher
text:
Since writing the review below I know see Dr. Pirouz. He is an excellent Dr with a great bed side manner and truly caring and compassionate Dr. I've now been treated by Dr. Untal, Levitan, Woods & Pirouz. Dr Woods, while very skilled & knowledgeable, was the only one that I did not connect with at all.
Dr Levitan is my treating surgeon has been very easy to work with and extremely caring. He had provided medications, referrals & epidural injection's for me. Recently he implanted a medtronics spinal cord stimulator in my lumbar spine. This has given me huge relief of sciatic pain and lumbra neuropathy. I'm scheduled for a cervical epidural again in 5 days, and while the surgery center can be quite busy, he and his staff are caring, comasionate and dedicated to whole patient care. I could not rate him highly enough.
I have also been a patient of Dr Untal and treated by Dr Patel who both have excellent beside manner. The nurses and techs in the surgery center have a stressful job and are usually extremely busy. They are often overworked as getting people out of pain or treating the pain is their priority so the schedule can be over-filled due to emergency procedures. I've waited 2 hours past appointed time and been seen immediately.
Patients like me, who are in intense pain or chronic severe pain, are often short, curt, rude and can be disrespectful. The Dr's nurses and staff have still remained calm, cool and collected.
Candy & Connie at check in work long tiring days and yet they too know that the goal is to treat everyone fairly.
In my opinion most people that have low rating of pain management specialists is due to the wait times they have experienced and not the quality of care.

name: Robbin Arcega
text:
I never thought I'd be the person to consider the gym a happy place, but that's what the San Bruno UFC gym is to me. I've been to a lot of general purpose gyms, and I've been trying out a bunch of different classes for years (from tae kwon do, judo, ice skating, yoga, kendo...) to hopefully find the one sport for me. On top of that, I also needed to be in a place where I felt comfortable.

The folks at UFC are nice, but chill. It's not the kind of vibe you feel at places like Crunch, where everyone seems to be almost manically cheerful and YEAHHHH FITNESS!!! The overall feeling here is, "Hey, how's it going? Gonna punch things? Cool, we'll be here if you need anything. We'll also play some jams."

If you like classes and have the discipline to go every day or every other day, you'll get super tired, but will probably be super fit. I'd been going consistently for about six months, tried out personal training, and I actually have muscle in my normally noodle-arms that's noticeable. They are TONED, yo. There's also a decent selection of weights and treadmills if that's your jam, but I mean, personally, it's all about the punching bags.

I started off month-to-month, and loved it so much that I went for the full year. I've just renewed my membership, and now that I live closer, I can go more often! Woo hoo!

resp.text:
Woo hoo! back at you Robin!
Thanks for your awesome endorsement.
Also thanks your great description of the gym and your experience here at UFC Gym San Bruno.

name: Beth Austin
text:
Dr. Amy and her husband made this difficult process as easy and comfortable as it could be given the situation. Just like the others, it was time to put my golden retriever down. She absolutely hated the vet (had anti-anxiety medicine, it was that bad), I couldn't imagine putting her through that stress for her last moments on Earth. She was comfortable on her dog bed and with relatively little notice, Dr. Amy showed up and helped ease our girl's pain as quickly as she could.

I am eternally grateful for the service she provided my husband and me (and everyone else). Not only was it better for our dog's sake, but our own. I cannot imagine trying to have to drive home after going through this. You can tell by the way she conducted herself, she has a true love for animals and respect for this process. She actually made me feel better.

I will strongly recommend this service, namely Choice Veterinary Care & Dr. Amy, to every single dog/cat owner I know. Thank you again for everything.

name: Darcy Segura
text: Dr. Michelle was so caring on the phone and Dr. Elizabeth and her assistant were wonderful in home, and made the process as easy as losing your fur baby could be. They were caring, compassionate and let us take all the time we needed. I highly recommend Choice Vets if the time has come to have to put down your dog.

name: Stephanie Hwang
text:
Our family cat had been suffering w/ hyperthyroid and kidney failure for some time.  We had opted out of treating because he was semi-feral and did not take to us sticking tubes down his throat every day.  Instead, we tried to make his life as easy as possible and when he got picky with his food, my mom fed him people food.  However, after a couple of years of this, we got the feeling the end was near as food (even people food) become unappetizing.  We had heard of services which would come to you so you could say goodbye to your pet at home where he/she is most comfortable.  One of the volunteers at Kitten Rescue recommended Choice Veterinary Care.  We had called another place recommended by another vet but Choice seemed to be more informed and knowledgeable.

We are incredibly grateful for the vets at Choice.  We spoke to Dr. Amy at first to discuss our situation and she made us feel comfortable with our choice.  Because the team at Choice are all vets, they all know about the various illnesses afflicting the cats and were very helpful explaining our cat's behavior.  We have known for a while that our cat was not going to get better and we wanted to make sure he had gotten the most quality life possible w/ the least amount of suffering.

Dr. Peter was assigned to us and he was incredible patient...he explained again how our cat's illness had progressed and made us feel comfortable with our situation.  He explained the whole process of how the euthanasia would work.  When the time came to say goodbye, he was so gentle with our cat.  A week after the euthanasia, a member of the Choice Team dropped off our cat's ashes in person.

There is really no easy way to say goodbye to a loved family member but we felt so supported by Choice.  Our goal was to have our family cat suffer the least amount possible and taking him to a vet would have been too cruel and stressful for him.  By the end, our family cat really had the best relationship with my mom so it was hardest for her.  She was just so incredibly grateful for the care provided by Dr. Peter.

text:

I decided the best option would be to have in-home euthanasia. My little girl was not scared but very comfortable at home . I thank Amy Stillwell-Graiff and husband for being so caring and kind . Having her transition at home is the best choice you can make for all the love and dedication, companionship this little fur babies give us. I own a pet store and I will sure will recommend her highly to my customers, by the way this is my  4th fur baby she has help me transition in my lifetime. Thank you Dr Amy and your team, you are an Angel!!!
Leslie & Sherrel

text:
My 23 month old knocked a front tooth loose on Labor Day. My dentist recommended Dr. Nasibi and gave me the contact information, as he felt a pediatric specialist would be best to handle the situation.

The office responded within 90 minutes to my text on a holiday (wow!) and got us an appt the very next morning.

The office has clean, child centered decor and the office staff was friendly and welcoming.

The hygienist was quick and efficient with xrays (as my kiddo was NOT very cooperative) and also very friendly.

Dr. Nasibi was very clear in his explanation of what was going on, the treatment plan, follow ups, and what we should expect at home. He was also reassuring to me, as I was pretty stressed out about the whole thing.

I definitely recommend Montebello Children's Denistry!

name: Denise Fernandez
text: If I could give this place zero stars I would. Let me start by letting you know the REALITY of what your experience might be like if you visit this office. WARNING do not take your children here! Most of the reviewers have one review which most likely means this office asked them to do a review remember that when yelping or googling places. The more reviews you make the most likely Yelp or google will keep your reviews. Our good friend is a dentist however, unfortunately does not work on children. He referred us to this dentist thinking he was an upstanding dentist who would treat us well and give my daughter a great experience. Our first impression with the doctor was good. He was nice so was his staff. The problem came once the exam was done they told us the insurance didn’t cover this and that. Which was a lie. Spoke to insurance myself and they stated the office was wrong. I also do dental billing so I knew they were wrong but wanted a verbal confirmation from the insurance. I took her to get a second opinion at Dr.Fishman’s office in Downey. Now this office was 100 percent honest. Told me they would never do the treatment that Dr.Nasibi at Montebello children’s dentistry recommended on a child. They said it was “aggressive” and there was no need for it some were put on “watch” meaning the dentist would keep an eye on them but she did not feel so much treatment was needed. He had recommended baby root canal baby crowns filling over 1000 dollars worth of treatment. Left Dr.Fishman’s office with her cleaning done and two fillings done have had no problems since. This was a while back. What reminded me was recently spoke to our dentist who is our personal friend and he stated to me that he spoke to Dr.Nasibi and he stated “they don’t know”. We may have not gone to dental school however, my dental background is what made me question his diagnosis and I was right!! Imagine those parents who just want to do what is best for their children and get lied to or pressured into doing something their child doesn’t need. This doctor should be ashamed of himself doing this to children. Do not go here do your research before trusting someone with your children. They do not let you in the room so who knows what gets said or done to your kids as well.  Plenty of offices let parents in treatment rooms.

name: shelly sussman
text: This was our first time ever confronting a rodent problem. It made us very squeamish and frankly grossed out. We called RCI and within a few hours Lee showed up to assess  the situation. He did an extremely thorough investigation outside and inside the house and came up with a game plan all the while making us feel very secure and in very good hands. Lee and His crew showed up the following day ready to go to work. Lee was here most of the time supervising and making sure everything was done and done well. He provided me with pictures of the work done throughout the house. Excuse the pun but it was not Mickey Mouse. It was very professionally done. In stark contrast to our horrible problem Lee and his crew were very well groomed and immaculate. Which is some thing that made us feel much better. We really felt like we were in good hands. I feel very secure about choosing RCI. Looking forward to a quick and pleasant outcome.

resp.text: Thank you, Shelly! Please let us know how we could assist you in the future.

name: Michele Kingston
text: I just purchased a new roof and 1 day in we heard him. By the morning he'd eaten the AC wire. I called Rodent Control and Judith was great, scheduled me the next day.  The next day Leo showed up...I didn't want to hear what he had to say honestly I was beyond stressed by now and he remained patient, calm and kind. My senior mother lives with us and Leo got them to fit us in the day after next. The next morning Gil called because they had a cancellation and made my mother a priority. The guys spent all day rodent proofing, then they cleaned, sanitized, repelled and set traps. They'll be back to check the traps and the work is warrantied. text:
We went for boba drinks, which were perfectly fine and prices were quite reasonable. They have some tasty-sounding sandwiches on their menu which we might try next time.

They have somewhat unusual hours for boba because the location is in an medical office building - at the time of this review they close daily at 3p and aren't open on the weekend (edit: right after I posted this I saw that they are open on some Saturdays this holiday season). Also note that it is on a one way street that is effectively an El Camino frontage road. We got there around 1:30p on a rainy Wednesday and there was no line. The building does have a parking garage but I didn't look to see if it is controlled or not. We were able to find parking on the street right out front without any trouble.

I would probably rate them a 4+ - my palate for tea is not that discriminating so it might not be possible for a boba place to distinguish itself enough to get a 5 from me based on quality alone. But with the favorable prices, the very friendly staff, and our hope for the success of this independent local business, I'll give them the benefit of the extra partial star. We'll be back.

name: Nathalie B.
text:
SDC took over my move from San Diego to Germany. The interactions during the invoicing process were fast and friendly, and I received an acceptable quote, well within similar offers. The move day got rescheduled on relatively short-notice, but the movers arrived on time on the final day of pick-up. They packed everything really well, and nothing arrived broken. Once my shipment arrived in the destination harbor (Rotterdam) SDC stopped responding to my emails, and I was lucky that they were working with a responsible agent in the Netherlands who would communicate with me. It is a big stress factor for someone to be giving all their valuable possessions to strangers showing up at their house for a lot of money, and then not hearing of the status of the shipment for full 3 months. An update, a vessel number, a container ID, anything would have been reassuring.

A big issue for me at the destination was that the movers contracted by SDC packed my already disassembled furniture (Ikea, mostly) by size of pieces, instead of by furniture item. When I tried to reassemble my furniture at the destination, we realized that we would have to deal with a massive puzzle if same-colored wooden pieces from a total of 6 different furniture items. A huge headache.
SDC did keep my belongings safe, but communication was minimal. I recommend keeping customers more in the loop for higher client satisfaction.

text:
The service I received from SDC has been frustrating, negligent, and possibly borderline illegal. I would strongly recommend anyone looking to use them for their relocation, to reconsider and find another provider.

My workplace transferred me to the Netherlands from California for a period of one year. Relocation expenses, however, were only partially reimbursed by the company. I decided to use SDC to ship my furniture and belongings, with an upfront payment of $2500. Four months after arriving to the Netherlands, I still was not able to get belongings. Trying to reach them by phone or e-mail was frustrating: At times, they ignored me. Other times, they promised a delivery date but subsequently canceled. Eventually, I was fed up and decided to drive to Munich and get some essentials from their warehouse - at MY expense!

Even after that, I haven’t heard from them, and they did not attempt to coordinate another delivery. Giving up on getting my belongings, I ended up purchasing furniture for my apartment, again at my own expense.
More recently, my year in Europe ended and I was transferred back to the US. I now called them, again, to get my belongings shipped back to California. Instead of apologizing for their negligence - and possible breach of contract - they informed me that I am liable for $3000 shipping, and tacked on a 600 euro “storage cost”. As you can imagine, I am extremely disappointed, and I will be exploring my legal options.

name: Norig Karakashian
text: I don't know who the man managing the dutch door is, but he was very rude to me today when I showed my receipt to ask about an outgoing international shipment that I made on the prior day at this same post office. The problem was that the receipt states "Tracking unavailable to this destination country" even though I paid the additional 16 dollars for the Registered option on my First-Class Package International Service to Spain. (I presume the discrepancy is caused by the COVID-19 crisis that is present as I write this review.) Nevertheless, I also had ready on my smartphone the USPS Tracking webpage for this package. When I asked the man how I could verify the delivery of this package -- considering that I paid for the tracking service -- he said that the information is online. When I proceeded to say that I did check online but didn't see any information, he loudly interjected, "No!" as he circled the customs form number (tracking number) printed on my receipt. I then showed him on my phone the freshly loaded USPS Tracking webpage that stated, "Not Trackable - USPS Tracking® is unavailable for this product for SPAIN." He became frustrated and questioned if I had typed the tracking number correctly, and then I informed him that I actually copy-pasted it directly from the electronic USPS receipt that I had elected to receive via email, in addition to the paper receipt. He then said, "I don't know what's wrong with your system, but I see it tracking on my end." I informed him that I simply purchased the service on the previous day at the retail counter in very next room of this building, and this is the only information I received. He angrily went to the backroom for about 30 seconds and then came back with a printout of the package's status reported by Product Tracking & Reporting (a system in the USPS Tracking Intranet). I was content with these printouts and took them for my reference (after all, the recipient of my package deserves some evidence of progress in case of a query). Finally, I thanked the man and exited the post office. I don't understand why this had to be difficult; I don't believe I deserved his negative attitude when all I did was ask politely about the tracking information that was absent in my only available sources.

name: Felix Lee
text:
Not too many people know about Scarantinos because of its obscure location next to the 5 freeway at the El Toro exit. Did you know that Scarantinos is a family-operated restaurant that uses Sicilian recipes handed down from the previous generation? In fact, many of the recipes were created by Grandma Scarantino over 50 years ago and remain unchanged.

The restaurant is split in half. On the right, there is a tablecloth setting in a casual atmosphere. Lighting is a bit dim. On the left side, a mini sports bar is found. There are 8 large screen TVs screening ESPN and Fox Sports, sometimes with games featuring local teams. The contrast in the two sides of the restaurant is striking, as a semi-intimate dining area is connected to the rowdy sports bar equipped with a jukebox.

The sports bar area is a bit divey. I came for a late lunch and groups of regulars lounged around with beers, chatting with the hostess, seemingly not having to go back to work. On the other hand, I was there anticipating a quick in-and-out lunch and even rushing my order, so I was an outlier.

What makes Scarantino stand out is their affordable $6.95 lunch special. It includes a generous basket of garlic toast and sourdough bread, soup or house salad, and a lunch portion pasta. The pasta is customizable although choices are basic. Meat or seafood toppings requires an additional fee. For the pasta, you can choose between angel hair, linguine, penne, and fettuccini. You also get to select a sauce between spicy marinara, marinara, pomodoro, and alfredo.

I ordered the linguine with spicy marinara sauce. Very rich tomato sauce with a fair amount of heat, texture was not creamy, taste was not overly sweet. Wouldn't mind having it again although I want to try their pomodoro sauce next time. Despite not having meat in the lunch, I left fairly full, probably because I ate the entire basket of garlic bread, which is one of the best I've had.

name: Mr. Gonsalves
text:
I was once a child at the age of 7 when my mother was taken home to heaven behind drug use/chemicals/violence/ and street lifestyle. Sacramento Police/Sheriff, and Investigators decided to call for a Sacramento Child Protection Services to take my sister and I there to the Receiving Home to be cared for because we were homeless due to my mom's addiction and lifestyle. That was in 1982. Since then my life had its up's and down's because of my teaching and behavioral traits I received from a toddler and those in chose to hang out with and the environment that I lived in incarceration was a big part of juvenile and adult life. Today I am a happily married man to the most beautiful woman and my best friend. I have 10 kids, a lovable dog, and we own our house that we live in happily in Sacramento, CA. I want to thank the Receiving Home for all they had done for my sister and I at that time and for the kids that have gone through there and those that are their now. You are all appreciate your hard work and passion that you make possible for those who need the love we need most at those hard times. MAY GOD BLESS YOU ALL.
Sincerely,
Johnny Gonsalves

P.S.
I thank God for HIS works in and for me. Today I am a leader of my Church and I help and am in service to those that have experienced hardships as I have.

name: Dan A
text:
They did some vinyl wrapping on my vehicle and the entire experience was not good. I was told 8am Friday and showed up to find out they open at 9am. At 9 when they opened I was told Matt told me the wrong time and he wrote me down for Saturday. When I saw Matt hours later my vehicle had not even been touched and he blamed others for not doing proper scheduling when Matt did the schedule with me face to face over a week prior. I arrive back later still with no communication to see a large scratch on my vehicle and I point it out before I even touch my key fob. He told me it came like that and walked away. I know this is not true since the vehicle is brand new and was PDI last week. I go to the office to talk to him more about the scratch and that the wrap is scratched up and marred. He tells me “let it be in the sun and it will smooth out” and I then say how is the other side perfectly smooth in the shade? He says to give it time. I now realize there is truth in the negative comment on here and Yelp. I wish I read reviews before I had them do any work.

Within hours I received a reply from this business after my review was published. So I apologize if I was  if I was mistaken on the names since I do not know these people and why would I schedule an appointment with this business on a day the vehicle would be 100 miles away?

resp.text:
Deleted my response because it stated the truth ,  we don’t book appointments for 8am, as we don’t open till 9am. Also your appointment was for Saturday . Like I said in my previous response, I have camera footage of you booking the appointment with jason. I also have camera footage of you dropping the car off with the existing scratches , camera footage of you being rude and accusing us of scratching your vehicle .

The real story, customer came in asking for his fuel doors to be wrapped because in his words his “dumbass dad” keeps scratching the car. The car had multiple scratches on both sides, far from being a “ brand new immaculate car” . As soon as he comes to pick it up he immediately walks right up to the car and blames us for scratching the car.

Now , if the customer would of acted like a civil adult , I could of easily polished out the scratches for him free of charge. But if you come in for a $50 very small and easy wrap job, and act rudely, accuse us of damage, then I’m not going to offer you any sort of help. I will go above and beyond for my customers , to make sure they are satisfied and happy. We work on exotic and very expensive cars daily , we specialize in removing scratches from brand new cars that come marred and swirled.
