name: Cierra S. White
text: I'm being pretty nice with the 2 stars. Getting through the traffic on Friday night was terrible. Parking was $10, packed and the walk to the main gate was long (this was at 6:30pm). The food lines were ridiculously long, waiting 30 min or more, then waiting another 15-30min just to pick up the food/drinks. By 9pm, they were already running out of food. The kicker- the food was decent, but the prices were double or triple what they should be. $20+ for lukewarm lemonade lol. The potato swirl was pretty much just stacked potato chips on a stick. And they tried to give my friend some undercooked pancakes. What a joke. The only really good food I had was the peach cobbler frozen yogurt I got from I Scream Yogurt. Besides all that, it seemed like they forgot Covid existed too.

name: Helen Hoang
text:
Poorly organized food event. Went on Monday at 5:00 PM, and left 2.5 hours later due to heat exhaustion and dissatisfaction from the quality of food. There were a lot of food tents but each item took 30-45 minutes to get... We paid $6/ticket, $10/parking, and then the food inside there was overpriced as heck.

Hawaiian honey cone ice cream - $15
Mediocre fried wings, lemonade, potato twister - $20
Ube horchata - $7

The only thing I liked was the ice cream, the fried chicken was flavorless and plain. Potato twister was like $10? Lol.

The worst thing was that it was scorching, weather advisory hot, and yet there weren't any tents, cooling stations, or water stations. I couldn't believe beer was sold for $13 and water for $5 a bottle when they charge an entrance fee. This was such a badly organized event and I feel like they knew it.

Also, no covid restrictions at all...so many people unmasked but I can't blame them because it was ridiculously hot.

name: Lauren Pratt
text:
I usually hate to leave bad reviews in places, but this was ridiculous. They definitely oversold on tickets. $5 per ticket, $10 for parking and food was $20+ each vendor.

The lines were maybe 2-2.5 hours long, and they ran out of food very quickly.

There are NO Covid precautions in place, the website said there would be. But there was none. 90% of the thousands of people there were not wearing masks and there was no social distancing.

name: Kit Lau
text:
Folks aren’t lying. There are many reasons everyone is giving it one star. Parking is ridiculous. The waiting in line is insane. No Covid precautions. Prices were ALL HIKED UP.
If it was expensive but had no lines. Cool, I get it. If it was cheap and had long line, that’s fine. But the fact that it was a combination of all those things made this event a total dud.

To give you some idea:
Boba tea $8
Lobster with noodles: $40
Pasta with cheese: $23
Lumpia: $8 for a tiny tiny tiny child size order

The list goes on.

You’re better off supporting your local business elsewhere.

name: Katie Frost
text: The whole event was poorly planned. They last minute changed the start time so it was crowded as all hell. NONE of the vendors were selling water except for the Cal Expo bar (we were told by a vendor that the event organizers said the vendors couldn't sell water because the Cal Expo bar was). It was hot and all the lines were standing in the sun on the blacktop. There was seating areas under gazebo like structures, except they didn't put the tarps on them to make it shady. If it wasn't for the trees near by my cousin would have passed out. There were several people that were passing out in line from the heat and lack of water at the vendors. We probably won't be going again if they hold the event in the summer time again.

name: Stephanie Hall
text: I was unable to make it through any of the long lines. It was hot standing on the asphalt with no shade. There were very few places to get water. I heard about people getting sick from the heat. I spent $16 (ticket +parking and fee) and I got nothing from it.

name: Nicky Medina
text:
One star is being too nice. ..Parking cost more than entrance fee. It was way too hot to be standing on black top ground with hardly any shade or misters. The lines were unreasonable and the prices for food was even worse. I will NOT be attending this event again. I have gone to many food events and not offering a smaller portion for purchase, for multiple vendor sampling was disappointing. After waiting 40 minutes for two undercooked and bland skewers I was done.

A lot of food was sold out by Monday which was the day I attended. To make matters worse, the frog leg vendor must have not changed their oil the entire event because a walk by their booth alone mad me lose my appetite and finally left. I'll stick with carnival food before I ever come to this event again.

But more than anything the thing most concerning was that there was no security in sight. No one had to go through security checkpoints . No metal detectors no bag checks. And just massive open spaces over packed with people. Felt super unsafe. We left after an hour. They were greedy and greatly oversold this event in the middle of a pandemic. No social distancing no other covid precautions. Won’t be returning to any of their events.

text:
May I start by stating that it is almost close to impossible to ever get a smile from children or let alone an adult when the words "dentist appointment" is mentioned. Yet, that is what separates  Eagle Glen Dental from the rest. By no means am I saying that any other dentist office is horrible, but it sure would be extremely difficult to match the great and professional customer service and services that are provided by both the staff and doctors. The staff always has such a warm welcoming voice and the kindness in their voice is displayed the moment one walks through the doors. They are always willing to accommodate and assist in helping work around busy schedules.

My family and I have been seen by both doctor Dr. Pham and Dr. Soto for the past five years; gentleness, cleanliness, honesty, and genuine care are some of the many attributes that one can experience at Eagle Glen Dental. Thank you, Eagle Glen Dental for putting a smile back in the words "dentist appointment."

name: Aurora A
text:
I enrolled here in an effort to lose weight.  I was willing to pay for a personal trainer to do this but enrolling here is way cheaper and well worth it. This place has kept me fit and I enjoy it compared to trying to haul myself to the gym every day!

The teachers are really friendly and like to push you to the limit. If you’re a student, you get access to the facilities whenever you want as long as it’s open. You also have access to all the classes. The classes consist of: group kicking, sparring, grappling, tai chi, push hands, weapons sparring, Kickboxing, conditioning, and submission grappling. Most of them are 30 mins.

They have family discounts if you join together and have the same private lesson together. The school not only teaches you Kung fu but Tai Chi.  They also teach you respect and values that is applicable to life.

Adult classes are during the evening because many people work. I’m so happy to be a part of this community! The culture is great and their teachings are top-notch 👍 Tuition is not exactly cheap but you definitely get what you pay for.

If I were to move away I'd be VERY sad to leave the White Dragon community. I love it that much. I'm their biggest fan! lol 😅

Update: I lost 20 lbs being here.

resp.text: Hello Nicholas, thank you for sharing your feedback regarding the fee that is charged to cash a check for non-customers. There are a few options available to avoid the fee. If you deposit the check into your account with an external bank, we don't charge a fee. Additionally, you can open an account with us and cash or deposit the check free of charge. If you have further questions regarding this matter, please don't hesitate to reach out to Customer Service at 800.872.2657. All the best, ^Kim

text:
I was involved in a car accident in 2019.  I was struck from behind by a impaired motorist.  Drunk, high, maybe both.  He tried to flee the scene but didn't make it far.  I was injured in this accident and needed help in finding what options I had.  I checked out a few other offices along with Pines Salomon and did some research online into all of them.  After speaking on the phone with Pines Salomon I was confident that they were the ones for me and my case.  They were very nice but even more importantly they were honest and forthright with what I could expect and not expect going forward.  They worked with me to find the right care and rehabilitation for my injuries.  They communicated with me throughout the process and never promised more than they could deliver.  My settlement was more than I was initially expecting which was a direct result of my attorney Laura and I working together to get the best outcome possible for me.  She made me feel like I was the most important client they had.

I recommend this office to anyone who wants straight talk, professionalism and delivered results!

text: My 4 children and I were involved in a terrifying accident. The other driver was at fault.  We were t-boned at an intersection by another driver who ran a stop sign, totaling my new car. I was apprehensive about pursuing anything with the other drivers' insurance company and began researching accident lawyers in San Diego, Michael Pines was at the top of the list with multiple great reviews and I scheduled an appointment. After visiting with Michael Pines and his staff, I felt no need to continue searching. They immediately took my case. My children suffered minor injuries, sprains, cuts and abrasions that have since healed. I suffered a bulging disc. They sent me to some great doctors. I opted to avoid surgery and settle my case. Michael Pines office settled my case for the other drivers maximum policy limits. My children have also been compensated. I can't express enough what a relief it has been to not have to deal with the doctors, insurance companies or bills. I would definitely recommend The Law Offices of Michael Pines.

Showed up in 45 mins. WOW!!!  I repaired my network at our office in 30 mins. I used to use another company in the area. They were slow and milked us for every minuet they could. I won't be calling them again.   Thank you Computer Repair of Temecula and, thank you, Jim

name: Georgia Myers
text:
Jim is my hero!!! I recently had an external hard drive crash and thought I might die of depression when I realized I hadn't backed up my music files for at least 6 months (very irresponsible for a DJ)! I went to a few different places inquiring about recovery results and pricing, and I must say there are a lot of crooks and quacks out there!!! I decided to search for "external hard drive recovery" on Google and saw a bunch of positive reviews for Computer Repair of Temecula. I went with my gut that he was the right man for the job and I am so happy I did!

Jim was able to fully recover all my music files, and set me up with a new, more reliable hard drive! I told him it felt like a miracle. He is fast, efficient, and has very fair pricing. He is now my official go-to-guy for any major computer crises I can't solve on my own.

Thank you so much Jim!!!!

name: Violette Early
text:
I lloked aroud on line reading all the reviews and Jim with Computer Repair of Temecula and Murrieta has the best by far. I have a Mav Pro that can be really involved that I didn't just want anyone working on my Mac. I called other shops in the Temecula Valley and Computer Repair of Temecula and Murrieta are the ONLY ONES that are certified my apple. They did a great job. My Mac Pro runs better than when I bought it. Go figure!!

Thank you Jim with Computer Repair of Temecula and Murrieta.

name: Mary Rodriguez
text: I wish I could give zero stars. I have a move across country coming up in one week that I have had a trailer rented for more than a month. No alternative offers, no alternative locations, I'm just out of luck. Sorry, we're ruining your move and making things impossible for you, but, hey, we will refund the money we made you prepay." Awful. Be afraid.

name: adonai elohei-tzva'ot
text: Most excellent customer service!!! Open till 8 pm. Refills propane tanks. Has new ones for sale.

name: Dave Duncan
text:
5 stars for the actual sevice, 1 star for their communication system.
After calling the number for this my local facility I spent 39 minutes on a recorded hold system. I was just trying to find out if I could fill my propane tanks at this facility. I had been there many times before since it is 2 minutes from my home. But,  did not want to load 6 tanks onto my truck if their filling station was not working. Finally someone answered. A answering service. Darn! No direct line to the actual store!
Fortunately the person on the phone was super nice and helpful. She even called the direct line to the store but also got NO RESPONSE!  So I thanked her and went ahead and took a chance a loaded up my tanks.
I arrived in 2 minutes and pulled up to the filling area. They have a button you push to get someone inside to come out.
Someone came out within a minute.
This employee was very nice. She immediately began taking pics of each tank which is required to document that they are not outdated.
I unloaded and she filled each one and I reloaded back onto to the truck. Quick, fast and easy!
You can pay right there with your credit or ATM card. You pay by the total gallons that were filled and they fill them full. 3.29 a gallon. That's cheap!
I previously took my not totally empty tanks to Lowes or AMPM and switched for a full tank to be sure I had full ones for a special occasion and didnt want to run out.  Normally this cost is 20 dollars each.
6 tanks switched would have been $120.
This total cost was around $46. Great savings!
I've been to this place several times before.
Each time their employees have been professional,  knowledgeable and friendly.
The communications need to improve.
Most persons that didnt know what was available ( like filling of propane tanks) at their facility would not wait on the phone for 39 minutes to find out. They would search elsewhere for what they need. I'm sure they have have lost business due to this fact.
So a improvement in this area would be a asset.

name: Amanda
text:
"Climate controlled" means in the summertime it will be 90 degrees on the upper level and a chilly 85 degrees downstairs, "guaranteed".

Also, their online payment system had failed to populate the automatic and manual payments I made for about 6 months. During this time, I was charged a late fee (for one month: this was before coronavirus circumstances. During coronavirus no late fees were collected) plus a $50 lien on my storage unit. That would have been fair if I simply wasn't paying my rent, but the fact that this was charged regardless of the fact that it was a technical error on their part was not acceptable. They only credited the amount to my account after I complained about it. I shouldn't have had to do that.

Then there was this fun little set of facts:

If you have a padlock other than their own: They'll cut your lock and charge YOU $50 for a replacement.

If you don't want to buy their lock because you're moving out at the end of the month, that's a problem. You're not allowed to leave your unit unlocked or they'll put a lock on the door and charge you $50 for it.

If your storage room is empty, you STILL have to lock it. With THEIR padlock. Otherwise they'll charge you $50.

Finally, when it's time to move out, you won't get a prorated refund if you're moving out any day other than the day your rent is due.

So even though I want to keep ownership of the unit until the end of the month in case I need it for a day or two when my movers arrive (after all, I've paid for it), I can't do that unless I lock it... With their lock.

Update 7/15:
I don't see what right they have to lock my belongings so I can't get them when I've paid all my rent. But that's what they've done.

name: Marcie Clabaugh
text: The WORST PLACE EVER!!! stood in line for 30min till I said forget it . While ONE person checked people out and then leave to move the truck around. Then help people who would just walk up to her. Like really??? I've been to other U-Haul places and they have someone outside to check in trucks and a person who brings the trucks around and do the inspection with you. So had yo drive yo Moreno Valley to get a truck. Felt bad for one lady who stood in line for a truck that she was told was here that they didn't even have.

name: Lisa Ortiz
text: Great, Speedy Service! Not only can you rent a U-Haul truck and buy boxes, they also have Smog services at this location. They're friendly and fast service! I will definitely be coming back here!

name: whenda woolley
text:
Anyone who ever said they LOVED UHAUL, OBVIOUSLY was serviced by Alexander Moore at the Uhaul off Jefferson Avenue!
I say this because, until I had the honor of being assisted by General Manager Moore, I had decided "I HATE UHAUL!"
I was planning a move 90 miles long distance move (Downtown Los Angeles to Murrieta) and EVERY Uhaul representatives up until the moment I met Mr. Moore were EXTREMELY lackluster and devoid of human interaction skills. Moving is ALREADY STRESSFUL WITHOUT assistance! They messed up my pickup location (sent me 30 mins away), they gave me the WRONG size truck, didn't inspect the vehicle, ETC... all in all NO BUENOOOO!
I was livid that I had to return the ONE WAY rental the next day after traveling 90 miles with a FULL load and STILL had to head back to DTLA to COLLECT what couldn't fit. 3 feet worth of space MAKES A HUGE DIFFERENCE!
It was Halloween day and I previously promised my girlfriend we would celebrate our victorious move with nostalgia by tick or treating. We were supposed to be done the night before, October 30th. Little did I know what Uhaul had in store for me when I made that promise to her.
While standing in line at Uhaul to return the vehicle, I began to pray. I was SO FRUSTRATED and UPSET it was ALL I could do.
My prayers were answered when out of nowhere Mr. Moore appeared and took over the register and called me over. As soon as I explained my dilemma, he said "I am SO SORRY for they way this was handled, I am 10 steps ahead and I WILL TAKE CARE OF YOU!"
His empathy and TAKE CHARGE initiative were EXACTLY what I needed.
TAKE care of me HE DID! I was able to complete my LONG DISTANCE move with more peace afterwards. Before being assisted by Mr. Moore I wondered if "Uhaul's lack of customer service had to do with it not having any real competition? No need to rise above if you're ALREADY on top!"
That notion has since been replaced with "Uhaul needs to TRAIN better and be more selective in their hiring process. They need MORE LIKE MOORE!"
I am grateful Alexander Moore assisted me on Halloween day and changed my opinion of the company he represents so effortlessly well!

text:
Solid Chinese food, but nothing spectacular.  We ordered a pretty wide variety of items as a group:

-Chicken Chow Mein: This was my favorite item on the menu!  It was delicious and definitely hit the spot if you are looking for some delicious, definitely not good for you Chinese food. :)

-Mongolian Beef: Not so good - it was a little spicy, but not in a good way.  It lacked a lot of flavor and I wouldn't order it again.

-Orange Chicken: It was okay - It had a really great citrus-y taste, but overall it wasn't my favorite.  There was a lot of breading (or whatever they use for it) which made it taste a little off to me.

Overall, if I'm in Redwood city and looking for Chinese food to satisfy a craving, this place will do, but I won't go out of my way to eat here.

Meet some great friends while I attended this school, and absolutely love it. They're renowned in Fresno and one or if not the best truck driving school here. And I believe that, it's amazing, not too expensive, very affordable, and they train you with respect and courtesy the entire time. I love this school and will be back to see them from time to time. Thank you again Rafeala and Robert for everything. You helped me gain my confidence in driving after training me so well, and got me to pass on my first DMV skills/driving test. They're the best hands down. If you want to be a truck driver, head over there now. Don't wait. DMV is backed up until January so schedule your appointment before you start school or as soon as you do. Good luck fellow drivers. I wish you all the best of luck, and to Robert and Rafeala; I wish and hope the best for you guys and your great company. Keep up the great work! You're putting well trained and great people on the road. Just the type of people we need driving in this state.

name: Jo a
text: If your taking the time to read these reviews, that means your smart enough to research about a trucking school before you sign up. That being said, PLEASE do not waste your time or money at this make-shift place. Let me make this short, I paid $1,800 to utilize their equipment for training, more than 75% of the time their trucks are out of service. I had a scheduled DMV driving test and UNITED  did not have a truck for me to take the test in because none of the 2 trucks were operational. If your going through PROTEUS Rafaela will sign you in without you being their so the school can still make their money off you. If your expecting to get quality driving time on the road you'll be sadly disappointed. You get what you pay for!!!! Everybody their has to practice their AIR LEAKS test on a broken down truck that hardly turns on. I ended up going through Morning Star Trucking and got my CDL A FOR FREE!!!!!  I HOPE this was helpful. Don't find out the hard way like me and SOOO MANY OTHERS

name: Jose Velez
text: I got my CDL through United truck driving school and i can tell you its the best trucking school around. Went through workforce connection to pay for it and they end up teaching you well when it comes to skills they will show you and then let you do it on your own but if you need extra help they will help you just gotta ask. Gotta thank Rafaela, Teresa, and Robert they will teach you well and make sure you have it down. If you want to be tested on airleaks, pre trip, and skills to see if you are ready for the DMV or make sure you have it down they will test you just have to let them know. Other than that you learn on your own and at your pace. You also set your own schedule to, you can show up at any time you want at open times and at any open days. Boy im going to miss their trucks.

name: Dave LaRoux
text: Went in several weeks ago to test drive a car and liked it enough but not enough to be sold on it, but that was totally cool. I felt no pressure to buy the car or trade mine in. Zero pressure what so ever,  a very welcome change from experiences I've had in the past, especially considering the reputation of Folton Ave dealers. Ryan, Jake and Peter are definitely doing their best to change that reputation one customer at a time. Not only did they be super cool with me testing driving with no immediate intention to buy but they did it twice and were very patient with me after I harassed them with questions I had after the pre purchase inspection revealed some potential issues. After talking to numerous techs about the inspection result I felt good that the car was okay to buy but I later found that the 12 volt power nor the cigarette lighter worked. My bad for assuming someone at some point tested the accessory power, simple enough to fix with a replacement fuse though. Still they gave me what I wanted for my trade in but didn't install the floor mats nor remove the plastic from the floors  but my wife and I were on a tight timeline so that may have been a contributor. Minor issues in the grand scheme of things though. All and all I'm walking away feeling really good about the experience. Definitely recommend checking them out and paying attention to the review scores as not all Fulton dealers are full of con men.

resp.text: Thank you for the 5-stars, Dave! Customers like you are the reason we love doing what we do! We appreciate your business here.

Our lenders do use a variety of factors as part of the approval process, not just credit score, so depending on all the other circumstances regarding the deal, that can make things easier, or more difficult, depending on the individual situation.  I do not see any recent applications with your name on them, though.  Did you apply under a different name?  As the owner of the company it's important to me that everyone is treated right, and given a fair chance to purchase.  If we failed at that in your case I would love to hear from you and find out how, so that we may fix it, or at least improve the way we operate in the future.  Please contact me personally and let me know what happened, and how we can make it right.  -Ryan (916) 413-2399

Then the fun began. She had me write my information on a scrap sheet of paper because she has no idea where her sign-in sheet was. Seems odd, but ok. Then on my way out the door she yells that they only accept cash or check. Hm.. ok, sure. Inconvenient for a place that charges no less than any other, but fine. I leave with the expectation of being called within a few hours.

Finally, I receive a call 20 minutes later that my dog is soaking wet and in a crate because they had to pull her out of a bath due to her attempts to “bite” the groomer. I was requested to come pick her up and they were unwilling to dry her. My dog has been groomed countless times from several places and I’ve never received anything but praise. She’s NEVER showed aggression towards a human, so I can’t imagine how she was being treated if it’s true.

resp.text: Thank you for your feedback. All scheduled appointments are reserved exclusively for each patient. Out of respect to all our patients, we do have a 48-hour cancellation policy; the patient who might otherwise benefit from a last-minute cancellation or no-show could be you or family or friends. We understand certain circumstances may arise that require an appointment to be rescheduled (e.g. family emergency, sickness). Our $50 broken/missed fee is assessed only for patients with a chronic record of multiple missed appointments and/or last-minute cancellations. Unfortunately, like everyone else, our hygienists do feel under the weather some days; these occurrences are few and far between. To respect our patients and avoid transmitting any infection during a procedure, we may have to reschedule appointments to a different date as a result. We apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused.

text: Elite arms is by far the best gun store in the valley. I don't even live in manteca but i will make the drive out there just to give them my business. text:
One of our first post pandemic outings, and we're fortunate to dine at Brasserie SLO.  They have a good selection of beers and wines. At first glance their menu is not well-suited for vegetarians but they made up for it with many excellent starters, which we ordered quite a few: Barata with figs, Caesar (not vegetarian), Grilled Broccolini. For my entree, I had the Papardelle.  Finished off with a generous portion of their excellent pecan pie.  Everything was superbly prepared and tasted great.  We really enjoyed our meal in their courtyard.

Service was attentive and unobstrusive.  My only wish that they have maybe a few more vegetarian entrees.

resp.text:

Thank you so much for your kind review. We really appreciate you dining with us and our team would love to see you again in the future. We've taken your concerns regarding offering more vegetarian options to our Chef.

Team Brasserie SLO

name: Matt B
text:
I found Beverly Hills Jewelers though a co worker who recommended I check it out when I mentioned I wanted to buy a pair of diamond studs. My friend was there a few months ago and had mentioned they spent over an hour with her as she tried on many different sizes until she found the perfect one.
So I decided to give it a chance too. I went on a Monday afternoon after grabbing some lunch down the street and was just thinking I would take a look, nothing serious. The ladies there were super helpful and showed me a ton of earrings when I gave them my budget. They had such large selection that I was shocked when they brought out about 6 pairs of studs of different sizes for me to try.
After about 45 minutes or so, I decided I wanted 2 carats total, so 1 carat in each ear. They were super shiny and sparkly. I knew I had to have them. I decided then, I would go ahead and just wear them out. It just seemed so right to go ahead and purchase them. I knew if I didn’t do it now, it probably wouldn’t ever do it.
I get compliments left and right from everyone I know and I have referred tons of people to the store who also love their jewelry.

name: John Brinkman
text:
Saw Dr. Ching here and then had three wisdom teeth extracted by the oral surgeon Dr. Tran. Two of them had grown in sideways, so it wasn't a simple extraction.

But the recovery was smooth. The pain medication prescribed kept things under control and got me through the worst of it which was the first two days post-op.

After a week, the pain had almost entirely subsided. My sockets are almost completely closed off/healed over at the 2 week mark.

Follow the doctor's instructions and you'll avoid dry socket.

Also excellent care from the dental assistants/hygienist.

text: Horrible company, horrible staff, horrible app, horrible customer service. They don’t reimburse for gas so what you take home each week with taxes taken out is basically pocket change. If you actually get through to them on chat (they don’t answer the phone or text) you can negotiate for a higher price ($20-$25) but they give you attitude about it and they usually (90% of the time) give your ride to someone else. text:
Me as a driver, just get “URGENT DRIVER NEEDED’’ text message

Wich means I’m in my house, and they text me saying there’s this ride available you gotta be there in 5 minutes.
Sometimes the hour they send it’s even past meaning that even if I wanted I wouldn’t be able to make it, totally a mess!!

The app doesn’t work at all

I have no schedule at all

That’s all I get from them a simple URGENT text message , not knowing anything and how much I will be making everyday

Yes there’s rides that costs over $20 BUUUTTT...
As there’s no schedule for me, I might get lucky getting a ride but that’s all for the day JUST ONE RIDE PER DAY

Who can survive with less then $40 a day?

I just wish that they would have:

A app that works
A number that we can really talk with someone
A schedule with the rides for the week

Didn’t know that it would be like this

I wouldn’t have wasted my time getting my car inspected, doing a interview and going to a agency paying over $100 to get the trust certificate that they ask for, because without it you can’t be their driver!

text:
PLEASE read the reviews and take the empty waiting room as hint.
I had the crazy bug that went around early March. My throat was so swollen I couldn’t talk or breathe without coughing. I haven’t seen a doctor in quite some time so my insurance [MediCal] was valid but ancient. Therefore the clinics couldn’t find me in the system. MedNow ended up charging me $150 just to be seen, I paid because I was desperate and needed to be okD for work the next day. They told me I wouldn’t be billed unless I had a procedure performed. I agreed. I asked if they’ll let me know what counts as a procedure and they said yes. Two months later I get a bill for $500! Just for a cotton swab ($17) and a bloodpressure check ($8) but they charged addition hundreds of dollars for the VISIT. Want to know what I was “Diagnosed” with ? ALERGIES. I know what allergies are and this wasn’t it. A week or so later I went to a REAL DOCTOR AND GOT SITUATED AND HELPED! DO NOT TRUST THESE PEOPLE! I’d be surprised if they don’t sneak charges onto your insurance.

resp.text:
Athena,

California Urgent Care Center's hours of Operation are 9 am to 9 pm 7 days a week. We take our last walk-in patient at 8:45 pm to give the patient enough time to complete registration forms upon arrival. This ensures that all medical history is properly entered into our system and gives the Provider time to look over the patient's medical history before the patient is seen for their medical needs.  Our closing policy is stated on the front page of our website at www.californiaurgentcare.com. We do hope that you will visit us again in the future for your urgent care needs as California Urgent Care Center strives to provide the best urgent medical care to each patient within our community.

-CUCC Team

name: Michael Lampen
text:
Plenty to say about a great experience!

I took the plunge and leaned on Jessica and Sam to help me make some big decisions on an engagement ring.  I’m a hardcore shopper and leave no stone unturned especially on big purchases. Budget and value is a delicate balance and they helped me navigate that very well.  Jessica provided a first class experience for a custom ring and stone selection. She knows the trends and is very tactful.  She thought of every little detail and I’m glad I trusted her opinions. Sam shared industry and general knowledge I didn’t find despite exhaustive research.  Great guy all around. They made the process super smooth and actually fun. Provided pics of the build and were very communicative and accommodating throughout it all.

Would absolutely buy from them again but not planning on it!  ;)  What is a daunting experience for most guys they made it very positive. My now fiancé, loves her ring and stone!

I can’t say enough. Thank you both!!!

The earrings and wedding band I’ve purchased were custom made pieces and I’m thrilled with both. They’ll even repurpose jewelry into a custom designed piece.

name: Michael “Fishbits” Hraba
text:
My wife's original engagement ring and wedding band were heirlooms that were a stunning art-deco piece, but aged and brittle enough that during our active lifestyle, workouts, etc... the band would warp, and lose diamonds. Over the years, it finally became brittle enough to crack, and we decided to upgrade for our 10 year anniversary.  We're pretty modest people, and aren't well versed in jewelry, so as my wife took the reigns, I trusted her to find an appropriate spot.  We had a plan to go into the city, and somewhere near Union Square visit "Brilliant Earth", and as I am prone to do... looked them up on Yelp, and at the last minute cancelled the appointment.  It is obvious that this was a "turn and burn" style diamond supplier... ie they've all the diamonds in stock, and they want to push them out. It's not personalized, and although I am sure they do a fine job finding conflict free diamonds, it just felt too corporate, too high pressure, and simply put, not at all special. So, I do my research and lo and behold, I've not seen higher ratings for any business, ever. Here's why this is the greatest business I've ever patronized:

- Sam, Jess, and Aida are class acts. Warm, genuine, kind, earnest gentlepeople. It's not a sale, it's a relationship, and it's obvious the whole gang rather not sell you something than sell you something that doesn't fit your preferences.  Their ability to educate, inform, and have fun while they do it is really refreshing.

- Hospitality and service.... sparkling/still water during initial conversations and when we came into the store. Always welcoming and service oriented without being over the top. When we finished and picked up the ring, they broke out a split of Veuve! =) What a tasty treat to round out the experience.

- They'll show you where they do the custom work, and their hardworking jewelry maker, an old school Italian craftsman.  The work they accomplish out of that space is nothing short of miraculous!

- What's more, they're in the future! They've a 3D Printer that can create hard wax versions of your eventual ring, so that you can design the setting and ring exactly how you want. Because it's a 3D printer, they can reprint it and update your design as many times as necessary to get it precisely right for you. You will never, EVER walk out of this store with something that isn't absolutely perfect for you. It's amazing.

- Their communication is bonkers amazing. *THAT* is a hard nut to crack in this day and age, because its so often we are lost, as consumers, to bad work flow, and forgetful employees.  Not here.... they are so transparent, througough, and expert communicators.

- I am sure they've diamonds in stock, but do those diamonds speak to you? Probably not. They run the most informative and satisfying clinic on diamonds, their history, how they are rated, what cuts you might want, and what carats are right for you, and inform you of the in & out fashion trends.  It's fascinating how Instagram is informing the fads and trends of diamond interest.  Lucky my wifey is a trendsetter and outlier... she wanted a radiant cut, which isn't instagram hip as a cut right now, so it truly provided more bang for the buck.... more carats at less price than the other trendy cuts. BUT.... they will hunt the entire world for that perfect diamond, to make sure it fits your style and pocketbook. Ours was found in New York, but overnighted and to say we were blown away doesn't do it justice.

I am so impressed, to the point of exceeding character limits, & not being able to organize my thoughts properly.  The TL;DR of this is simple: Support this amazing local business, support these wonderful people who are basically a family of friends that get to charm and delight and amaze people with what they do, and how they accomplish it.

This is a relationship, & we're smitten. I've never been happier to spend money, because it's anchored by obvious passion and skill, talent, & honesty. We'll be back, time & time again. It's rare to find a place that is a no brainer, but here we are. Hugs guys!! =)

name: Eric Ascher
text: As always Jessica at Sausalito Jewelers delivered. I just bought a birthday present for my mom here and I got exactly what I was looking for. I have purchased several gifts from them as well as my fiancee's engagement ring. Excellent customer service and products. I will definitely be returning!

name: Christopher Wolfe
text: Brought a kinked necklace for repair.  They were straightforward and explained the risks and indicated they could fix it.  Came out perfect.  Would recommend for repairs!

name: melinda lieb
text: You are in the best of hands with Sam and his stellar team of professionals at Sausalito Jewelers. There is no one I would trust more, especially with heirloom pieces. From start to finish, Sam and Paolo, his master metal worker from Italy walk you through your options, whether you need to fix or like myself, start from scratch. I was hand-held through the process of redoing my engagement ring-- something I had put off for over a year; as I had discovered the previous jeweler who initially created my ring had cut corners-- so hard to trust someone with your valuables after learning that structural damage was irreversible, not to mention not heirloom quality as promised. Sam and Paolo went above and beyond to meet with me several times and went to great lengths to educate me in their process and next best steps to recover/redesign my engagement ring-- I gasped when I saw the result. It was the setting the stone deserved and was intended for, turning around what I considered an unforgivably unprofessional job and restoring not only my ring to glory but most importantly my faith in Jewelers.

name: Joshua Jones
text:
Fantastic dentistry! I hate going to the dentist. The thought pains me, just as much if not worse than going to the DMV. My 3rd visit is tomorrow and I couldn't be happier.

Dr. Anderson and his team have taken great care of me. The doctor himself is calm, cool, and collected which goes a long way to make me feel confident that my money, time, and self is making a good investment.

I'm currently visiting for a root canal that was more inflamed than needed. Instead of just rushing through the procedure the DR spread out the treatment plan over several days to allow my body time to heal and be ready for the full procedure.  No added fees for this. It's been smooth sailing and the final steps to come. Should something change I'll update this review but I doubt anything will go wrong.

I hope everyone else has as good of an experience as I'm having.

name: Ann Troxell
text: Its hard to give a 5 star review for a root canal but Dr. Anderson and his staff were great. Very organized and professional and no pain during the procedure. Good follow up and willing to answer any and all questions.

name: Jennifer C
text: Like many people today I found Dr. Anderson by online reading all of his positive reviews. I had a problematic tooth that had been through two failed root canals by another dentist. Dr. Anderson listened to the history and was able to successfully redo the root canal and treat the infection. He was very skilled and focused while he worked and incredibly, I felt no pain when gave me the Novocaine shots or during the procedure. He also called me after the procedure to check in. The office staff Ruby and Kelly were both kind and professional and followed up with an email report of the procedure that included an x ray of the tooth. I highly recommend Dr. Anderson for a root canal.

name: JW Chang Mayo
text:
I was referred to Dr Anderson by another great dentist (Martin Allaire, DDS ) for a root canal consultation. Judy at the front office was so welcoming, efficient and competent. His dental nurse Connie was a calm presence and so friendly. Dr Anderson was very gentle (had to administer Novocaine to complete his thorough evaluation), knowledgeable, and competent.   I was not a candidate for a root canal, but he immediately referred me to a periodontist. Dr Anderson, himself, called the periodontist's office to ensure I was able to make an appointment ASAP to resolve my tooth issue--Thank you, Sir!
Overall, the entire team was so professional and efficient. I highly recommend Dr Craig Anderson, DDS and his team. I am going to let my primary dentist know this referral was excellent.

name: L. Villagomez
text: I'm so grateful Dr. Anderson took the pain away from an infection caused by a root canal that was done incorrectly by another Dentist. He is precise and cares greatly about the recovery of his patients. Thank you Dr. & all staff!

text:
Gym fees set to withdraw on the 20th of every month. In July I requested the end of my month to month contract. Was advised I had to come in to cancel and as long as I did it before the 20th (when my billing is scheduled to hit, that I can cancel and nothing would be charged. I came in and they altered their office hours to a smaller window making it very difficult to reach someone. I came in a second time and spoke to an employee advising I want to cancel the month to month gym membership. She then advised me I needed to put in a 30 day notice. This wasn't explained over the telephone!!! So now they want me to pay yet another month of service and I don't agree! This is robbery. When customer service called me a month ago I told them this but they explained they only take the payment and NOT deal with membership. Awesome! So what's when I called the gym and asked how to cancel my membership. I've been a member for 1.5 years and have gone under a dozen times. My 12-month contract has been over! I've been month to month for 6 months. They took away a great perk that initially drew me in... A computerized fitness program. And not to mention they charge $15/ more than any other Anytime Fitness and have minimal machines. They should explain everything when asked over the phone and not come back with- this was told to you at signing (1 1/2 years ago) and shove a 30day notice in your face. I want my membership cancelled as it was explained to me over the phone and no more charges to my card.

Ohhhh and as much as they charge- they could use some AC! ITS HOT IN THERE!!!!

text:

But unfortunately the area doesn't seem to be the safest area for a person that is not from that area. The unit was not the best unit but management did painted and upgraded the unit very cute by also installing modern vinyl planks, nice trim, and modern kitchen knobs. The walls seem to have no insulation, so you can hear clear conversations from the neighbor. So I suggest management to propose the owner to invest on insulation. My recommendation is for management/owner to invest on a onsite security personnel for maybe 6 months on and 6 months off so good residents like my nephew  feel safe to stay in this property. You can also be part of the Riverside Crime Free Multi housing. I did not see any signs on the property that shows you are part of this program. It is a great program and any time there is a crime issue a pop officer comes to the property in no time.
I wish the best to this management company.

name: Kianna Snyder
text: We moved here just over two months ago, from their sister owned complex Latitude 33. We have really enjoyed how quiet and how pleasant the neighborhood is. We have easy access to all kinds of resources, grocery stores, shops, food and entertainment all within 5-15 minute drive. The price fits the complex, although the singular covered parking space included in the rent is a little unrealistic, especially for the people living in the two bedroom apts. Unless you work a super early or super late shift finding parking at peak times is extremely difficult, to the point where people block others in, park in fire lanes and generally are disruptive to others days. If you are okay with having to take some extra time to find parking or you only have one vehicle, this place is great! Plus they have been remodeling a lot of units and they are looking gorgeous and modern. Definitely feels more like home than our last apartment. I'll update again if anything changes. Jeep up the good work!

name: Drew Cover
text:
STAY AWAY, Awful.  Friends lived here for years and regretted it.  The niceness is a facade, 'lipstick on a pig' best describes this place.

Count on your rent going up like clockwork with predatory leasing.  Kiss your deposit goodbye, even if you have no pets and clean perfectly.  Don't ever count on maintenance to give you the time of day.  They change guest parking rules without telling tenants, your friends and family will be towed.  Even the tenant parking situation is terrible, you're usually double parked.  The walls are paper thin.  Cooling an upstairs unit is incredibly expensive.  And the area smells bad from something, I think its the smell from the waste water plant...  Finally, OVERPRICED!

STAY AWAY!  How do I give zero stars google??

When you're about to sign that lease, look the the $ amount and then remind yourself, "This is for an OLD apartment in a large complex in ESCONDIDO"...  Then make the right decision and WALK AWAY.

4/12/21 Note: this review is for the temporary covid vaccination site established at this location.
The vaccination site is very well organized with volunteers guiding candidates every step of the way. My appointment was at 10:45 and I was done with the shot at 10:53. You need to wait another 15 mins under observation for any reactions from the vaccine. There is a tent set up and seats are socially distanced for safety. Water bottles and candies are provided as well.
The site requires prior appointment and you need to have a consent form, a copy of a valid ID and your insurance.
This is a super smooth operation.

Many are varietals that one rarely finds outside of Italy. Scratch Kitchen had his Merlot as the only merlot they served.

Antonio has great pairings of cheese and cold cuts in his tasting room.   Come sit on their patio and enjoy either a tasting, flight, or abottle amongst friends. The hard part of course, is leaving!

name: Tim Newton
text: Well I don't know what to say. I did read others reviews concerning this doctors bedside manner but decided to chance seeing him anyway. There is only one reason I did, I need clearance for hip replacement surgery. All things considered I am a pretty healthy 57 year old man. He wanted to start a series of tests that would have to be completed on different days. I told him I could not afford to be running back and forth. His only response was that the insurance would not pay to have these tests done in one day. I knew then that it was all about the money only. There was no concern on the patients part. I asked what test I would need to gain clearance for hip surgery and told me I only need the Echo cardiogram test. As it were he was going to order all kinds of tests just to find something wrong with me. Why don't doctors find what's right and then build on that? With a new hip I'll be able to exercise and function pretty much at a normal level for me. I for one will not just lay back and let doctors pump be full of pills and then tell me I'm sick. I used to like my primary care doctor but he's going to get an earful when I go to my next appt with him. I don't recommend this doctor at all. I think it's time for him to hang it up. All in all I had a very cold unwelcoming experience from the get go.

text:
April 2017 It was a long grueling process but I'm glad it's finally done and I'm approved and got keys to my new place. I'm so very thankful and appreciative. Homelessness is no joke and very depressing. I can breathe and live again and me and my 9 month old finally have a place to call our own. So thankful for wakeland for developing it and Saira, Jennifer and Nathaniel for all their hard work getting all these files processed. And I guess next week and throughout may 100 more units will be filled. Lol it's gonna get hectic as heck. Now there's only about 40 people, well 40 units occupied so it's quiet but when those next 100 units of probably average 100 to 300 people c come in haha no more calmness lol. But anyway very nice apartments. Color is earthy, light yellow walls and greenish brown tile flooring. NO carpet btw. And my kitchen is along side the wall but hey can't complain I have I FINALLY have a home.

April 2019 Update we have new management as of January 2019 manager came in and February 2019 assistant manager came in. They're Meh. You hardly ever see the manager which is bad. Deliberately avoids you on elevators. She didn't take the first elevator with me which is closest to staff parking anyway she walks to the double elevators. Um ok. Hardly see her anyway at least with Maeisha we saw them alot I kinda miss the old management. These are more by the book which is not always a bad thing. Just doesn't feel connecting like meesh and Jennifer were. See I even called her meesh :(
Lol. It is what it is.

Dec 3rd 2019 Edit again to say I notice many residents have multiple cars and I notice many residents have brand new Mercedes Benz range rovers trucks. The family that owns the Mercedes Benz I seen have the children's father show up and guess what he owns a Mercedes Benz as well. Like what the heck?? I thought this was a affordable housing complex for the lower income people. Those people don't deserve to live here and my sister came up with a good answer as to why they have all that is because they lied to get in this place they make more money than they are reporting. And that makes since and is not right for those of us who desperately need a place to live. Now this new management is by the book and on stuff so I'm sure they have a way of finding out. Otherwise if those people with the brand new range rovers and Mercedes Benz really are low income than their spending ALL they money on they car. A oil change alone for a range Rover I found from someone who owns it they said cost them $400-600 I said SAYYYY WHATTT!? just for one oil change you got to be joking. So anyhow there's no way the residents here are low income with cars like that that require such high maintenance. Again if they are all they money is going to they nice cars. To show off but live poor. Anyway that's my update again as a resident here. Also residents smoke when management is gone and on weekends. They also park in management parking after hours and on weekends as well LMAO what a way to really take advantage. And some may not know that the assistant manager and 2 maintenance men live at atmosphere as well. But I guess since it's after hours and weekends they are residents just like us and don't enforce or I could be wrong maybe they do but that they can't complain to everyone and also it's their time off to enjoy themselves. Anyhow I still think it's great place to live despite those that don't belong here. There's still ALOT of really cool people. Some who've I grown best friends with.

Will update again if needed lol.

It's new, has new everything--and kept very clean. There is a shower room that is very clean and big enough to get ready if you have to run off somewhere immediately afterwards. Plenty of lockers to keep belongings (BYO lock) and a water spout.

Staff is lively even at the wee morning hours! They are helpful if your HR monitor cuts out before or during the class. Coaches here took me a while to get used to for some reason (maybe it's because I come in at 6:30 a.m. I am totally confused by the happiness), but now I look forward to their enthusiasm about working out! I have had DJ, Arielle, Gregg, and Tyler: if you like consistent and efficient explanations/help, go with DJ; if you like super duper pumped and enthusiastic/inspirational go with Arielle; if you like also pumped and enthusiastic go with Gregg; and if you like kind of offbeat, hilariously wacky and fun go with Tyler. Seriously, despite the range of styles in coaching, they are all helpful in creating an environment for great workouts.

Parking has to be validated (structure shared with Olive Garden/BJ's/CPK/etc.); one con is if you come in the afternoon/evening you WILL encounter a lot of dinner traffic and the lot is a nightmare at that time.

name: JayR deGuzman
text:
I'm not a regular Yogi/Yoga Practitioner, but I was looking for an opportunity to build up on my flexibility and core strength after coming from an Achilles Rupture Surgery.

With that said, this studio is exactly what I was looking for. I've only taken a few classes of the 1-week free trial so far,  but was already interested in coming back regularly after my first class. The classes I've taken are "Yoga Sculpt" and "CorePower 2".

Yoga Sculpt is like going through the yoga flow with weights, cardio, and strength training.  "CorePower 2" is the general Yoga class, but more demanding on the body than the previous level classes I assume. (Honestly I can't say since I haven't tried CorePower 1 or 1.5) Either way, both these classes will be as taxing on your body as you want it to be depending on how much you challenge yourself.

The instructors I've taken classes from are Jackie, Melanie, Roxy, and Kalista. The passion in their practice definitely shows in their classes. Each staff member is very inviting, encouraging during class, and will put you to work while at the same time being mindful of your body, mind, and spirit.

Like I said, I'm no Yogi, but whether you're looking for a place to practice Yoga, or push your body's physical fitness level, CorePower Yoga at Golden Circle definitely delivers!

Decor is similar to the other locations but more open and inviting. There is a small outdoor patio and part of the bar seating is exposed to the outdoor area which you don't see very often. Live music is also featured on Thursdays in the lounge area by the bar.

My husband and I ordered two drinks (one beer which was part of the "Wednesday: Take the Glass Home" special and a new cocktail). I ordered the Floor is Lava cocktail which features mezcal. It was smooth, refreshing and delicious. We also ordered a side of signature fries that paired well with our drinks.

Overall experience was wonderful and we look forward to coming back again soon.

- Coverage, should only take 1-2 coats to cover versus others that need multiple coats.
- Longevity, this new paint job should last  you years to come
- Color Lock Technology, if you picked a rich/deep color, the color lock technology Benjamin Moore has will allow the color to stay true to its color for years to come without fading.
We hope you enjoy your new color in your home for many years to come.

name: Louisa Toy
text:
Cute, little restaurant that sells the fun Japanese rice balls. I love the Japanese rice balls (onigiris), and was so excited when I found this place! The restaurant itself is pretty small, so it may not be the best place to sit down and eat. But really, rice balls are great to-go snacks, so it's convenient to take them around. $3.50ish per onigiri- not too bad.

Since I was ordering to-go, I went off the menu that was posted on Yelp, which showed a very limited selection. When I actually walked in to pick up the food, I found their extensive menu sitting on the counter. I was so sad to see they had many more flavor offerings than what I had seen online. Bummer. With that said, I still ordered quite a few to try (not by myself, of course).I tried the spicy tuna (very good), salmon (very good), teriyaki chicken (not bad), and curry chicken( not bad). I wish I had seen the beef and pork belly (in the larger menu). I would've loved to have tried those. Anyone who has tried those flavors, let me know how it is!

name: Teddy Bear
text: So let me begin by saying that this location is used as a lot for Fair. I originally had a review on here but was pressured by Matt from fair and the owners of rolling motors to remove my review. The owners are clearly apart of what’s going on with fair at their location. It took the better part of two days to get a car that I had a reservation for. They could not and would not provide ample enough vehicles for the demand that they created. Communication Is nonexistent and the vehicles seem nice but the one they gave me had a bad break. They gave me a Uber inspection form signed by their mechanic stating that it passed Uber’s requirements mechanically and safety wise to be used for transporting passengers. They clearly falsified documentation and when I tried to contact fair yesterday they We’re closed despite stating that they are open 24/7. Upon contacting the maintenance program I was told that brakes were not covered and then when contacting fair today I was told that I would have to contact the warranty department and if they won’t cover it it is an out-of-pocket cost to me to repair the brakes. I have been around and around with this company and I am going to return the vehicle and walk away because it is nothing but garbage. Their policies and their procedures are unprecedented. You will be lied to you will be missed lead and you will be giving your money away while you waste your time. I do not recommend this company I do not recommend anybody that associates with them. Please if you’re reading this to not sign anything or give them any payment information.

name: Antonio
text:
I can't thank this company enough for their willingness to help, their friendliness and professionalism!  We've been struggling with pool issues for over a year so I contacted Leslie's to request a service technician to check out our system.  First of all, Manager Paula is wonderful.  She's super nice and super helpful and always a pleasure to work with.  The Service Tech that came to our house, Mark, was just OUTSTANDING!  Mark took the time to listen carefully to our concerns and then made it totally clear that he fully understood what we have been frustrated with.  Then he reviewed our system and showed us exactly why we were having problems, fixed issues right there on the spot, showed us exactly what he did and explained to us exactly what we need to do in the future.  Mark was professional, friendly, caring and really just happy to help us.  It was an absolute pleasure to work with him and such a relief to finally have the knowledge and tools we need to keep our pool sparkling.  HUGE THANK YOU to Leslie's Pool Supplies, Service and Repair and their outstanding staff!

Note - Issues we were having:
Pump and filtration system replaced 2 years ago and nothing but trouble since.  Black spot forming in pool.  We thought pump was too weak.  Tried several pool cleaning services, nothing getting better.

Mark showed us that our pump was actually much better and stronger than the original, issue was that it wasn't programmed properly and was only operating at about 65% of what the original pump operated at.  Mark reprogrammed the pump and showed us how we can reprogram as needed.  Also took care of a few other problems with our filtration system and identified the black spots as black algae and recommended a course of action that we're taking and all is looking up!

name: Jeremy Mahan

name: Clarice Neal
text:
D. Pautz did my Shattered elbow Surgery 2/2006 and then had to remove hardware in September 9/2006. I Thank Dr. Pautz in 2006/2007 for his amazing work & bedside manner. Then he disappeared...???... I heard awful rumors but when I saw his office next to Victorvalley Hospital...ALL I COULD DO WAS GET EXCITED TO FIND MY SURGEON !!!
But unfortunately 13 yrs later he told me I am as far as a surgeon can go...my extremel sharp stabbing pain that keeps me from working ,sleeping, & even doing basic duties around the house. I have never been able to brush my hair or put my hand behind my back since 2006 til last year with my amazing PT.
My only concern was that his solution was to insert a cortisone injection directly into my bone/elbow. I have nothing but bone on bone and that was the worst pain ever. I highly respect Dr. Pautz but when the words... "If you can handle these cortisone injections then there is no need for you to see me as your elbow is fixed and you will endure pain for the rest of your life...due to the trauma at the area from the car accident...But I surgically can not help you so theres no need for a follow up" Being He was the Doctor with all smiles & the greatest bedside manner....I guess 13 years can change a person. He no longer was that Doctor I was excited to see because everytime I had... he was there to help... It wasnt the reunion I had hoped for...even if there wasnt anything he could do. I WAS HIS PATIENT TWICE IN 2006 & I THANK HIM FOR ALL HE DID BACK THEN. NOW...??? Dr. Pautz I miss The smiles, Your amazing bedside manner, yes be truthful but now it's in a way I'm saying Not The Same Amazing Doctor.  If you still do wonders like you did with me... Shirts and other goods were all over the floor, people were running over them with their carts, and the quality of the merchandise, which looked more like the place was going out of business rather than just opening, was very poor.

They actually had better quality at the old Zody's, Akron, and today's Target and Wal-mart!

I found a few items to purchase, and upon going up front there was a line of about 15 customers waiting to pay!  I would not wait that long for the Second Coming so I left.

We will not go back to Burlington. I remember them when I visited White Plains, New York and it was a classy, clean store loaded with quality merchandise.  Something has drastically changed.

Avoid this place and go to Bed, Bath and Beyond, Target and Wal-mart.

name: Joe Loew
text:
The best service quality you're likely to find at any U-Haul. Problem? They'll find a way to fix it.

FULL DISCLOSURE: I am a former employee at this location, as well as a salvage mechanic in the shop behind. You may consider this bias, but I consider it a full view of what really happens when you rent a U-Haul truck!

U-Haul Centers (centers are directly run by uhaul vs. dealerships, which are private companies that provide U-Haul product) have rigorous processes for managing equipment rentals, and it is top-notch. However, you can't predict people.

Trucks go all over the country in unpredictable ways. Consequently,, service quality will vary, depending on the people executing those processes.

The best U-Haul centers --including this one-- have complaints. Look more closely, you see that some people just like to complain.

A good company is fair to EVERYBODY, which means that sometimes the answer is "no." Some people just don't like not getting what they want.

At this location, the people make all the difference, and you can be sure that you will get the best possible response in any situation. This can-do attitude begins with Lester Halla, the General Manager.

If you want good service and the most for your dollar, go to this location.  End of story.

name: Christopher Davila

name: Alexis Murray (BraveBurrito)
text:
I've used this store before with no issues at all what so ever. My last time was absolutely horrible!

I tried to send a package internationally in May. Shipping was shy over $150. It went a town over, and ended up getting delivered to my house, a month later, with no information given. I gave the UPS store a call to get information. They had no info. The best they could do is make a claim for a refund. They told me that this takes at least 30 days to investigate.

A month of no word, I give them a call. Still investigating. 3 months go by. The manager of the ups escalates it and should receive an update in 5 business days. I call a week later, still no update. I wait another month. Nothing.

About two weeks ago, I finally managed to get an update. My claim was closed a month ago, and done with. No refund. UPS associate told me to email my number over, and that they would forward it to the owner to give me a call.

It's been nearly 3 weeks since. No call. No resolution. I would strongly avoid this place. Multiple occasions they have hung up on me after having put me on hold for 20-30 minutes.

name: John Ca
text: Been using them for a few years and we've had many problems over that time. There used to be one nice staff women but she's gone now and its just a bad experience every time. name: Robert Novell
text:
I shipped a package through their store with a next morning delivery option. the package got out on time, but Ups corporate failed to get the package on the airplane.
The real problem is when I went into the store the next morning they said I was going to get a full refund. They took my name, number, and tracking number. They said we cannot process your claim until the package arrives tomorrow and they would call me to let me know the claim has been processed. Then I would need to wait 7 to 10 days for a check to be made out.  I failed to receive a call from them  regarding my claim and they are only open for another 3 hours. I called  and they knew nothing about my claim and gathered all my information again and said they would call me in 7 to 10 days when my check arrived. I doubt they will!

resp.text: Mr Novell We are sorry "UPS" failed to get your package delivered on the expected delivery date 5/24/17. We did process the claim after "UPS" delivered the pkg on 5/25/17 today. We called you today (as you stated above) to let you know that the claim has been submitted and that "UPS" will send your refund in 7-10 business days to our location. text:
I was looking for something very particular all around the Bay Area.  After coming up empty for a few months I found a stellar example at Vanquish.
They were more than helpful with letting me test drive the car and stop by as often as I liked to ask questions and look it over.

While that first car sold before I was able to pull the trigger, they just so happened to get a 2nd example in a few months down the road.  Once again, Moe (who runs Advantage as well as Vanquish Motors) was just as inviting and helpful during the entire process.

Highest recommendations to a shop that is zero pressure (huge HUGE plus when you have a wife that hates car salespeople...she loved Moe) and has a great, every changing selection (because stuff sells so quickly!) of vehicles.  Can't stress enough how little pressure there was; ZERO.

Moe is as genuine/honest as they get; when the time comes to purchase another vehicle Vanquish will be the first place I check.

Other Dealerships need to take a page out of this guys book. Thank you so much Moe! I will be back in a year or two. I expect to be able to buy my dream car around then(2006-2013 zo6 Corvette).

resp.text: A large part of our business is referrals from happy customers. We are disappointed that our efforts to help you have left you with a bad impression.  When you purchased the vehicle, we promised we would provide a brand new Key Remote  after the purchase and we did just that, as part of our customer service after the sale. After you called in November, about 4 months after your purchased your vehicle, and told us that your heater does not work, I asked you to bring it the following day. You said you would bring it on Monday. I said ok. You mentioned your A/C did not work from the day you bought it, which was in August, about 105 degree plus. When you called three weeks later we just said if you can not make it please let us know because the parts we purchase have a time limited replacement warranty and we do not want the warranty from manufacturer expire. By the way we do have a receipt that we put in new A/C compressor prior to you purchasing it. We assumed it was working since summer is gone and no complaints from you at that time. Without hesitation we said bring the car to fix. you got upset and we think maybe you thought we said no warranty or warranty expired whereas we were talking about the A/C compressor that we put on. You hung up and we called back right away and no answer. Asked Jonathan to call you since he was your rep and he said no answer either. We have the text that was sent right away by Jonathan asking you to come in, but you did not respond to any of our calls. It would be easier if you would answer our calls and get it resolved and repaired as we do for all our customers. Please contact us and lets get this issue fixed. We appreciate your business are looking forward doing business with you now and in future. If there is or was a misunderstanding we apologize and we will do our best to resolve your issue.

name: andy cota
text:
My former dentist,  who retired after 50 years, Dr. Au referred me to D. D. S. Lily Djie at Bonita Point Dental Arts. Dr. Au a stated, I would be in good hands. Immediately after entering the dental office, I was immediately greeted in a friendly welcoming tone by Hygenist Rose. Shortly thereafter I was taken to the dental room for X-Rays. The Dental Assistant Cindy also greeted me in the same manner as Rose, who explained the purpose of the X-Rays. The process was quickly done, each set of the photos taken of my teeth, was displayed on a screen to ensure the photo was taken correctly. Next, I  was seen by the Hygenist Rose, who also explained the process, as she cleaned my teeth she frequently checked on how I was feeling.
Then I was seen by D. D. S. Djie, who also displayed the friendly manner as her employees. She explained in a simple terms the condition of my teeth,  and she did not show signs of being in a hurry and took her time with me.

In closing I want to mention the equipment used are modern and the staff mannerisms are outstanding. If you are hesitant in seeing a dentist, your fears will be toned down after your visit to D.D.S. Lily Djie.

name: Angel Jauregui
text: I've seen several dentists throughout the years around San Diego and Bonita dental is by far the absolute BEST dental Office I've ever been to! Dr. Pascua and his team are awesome! From the front office to the dental hygienist to the dental assistants, this staff is very professional, knowledgeable and friendly. Last week was my first dental cleaning here and this week I had a cavity filled by Dr. Pascua. Both visits were great and I felt no discomfort whatsoever. I didn't even feel the pinch of the shot to numb my gums prior to dental work! Dr. Pascua took his time to apply the numbing cream and allowed sufficient time to numb area prior to giving the shot. It clearly shows that this staff takes pride in their service they provide. They definitely earned their top 5 star ratings! Dr Pascua and his team has earned a client for as long as they practice dentistry :)

name: Geena Fiorucci
text: I stumbled upon the hike to Crane Flat Lookout by starting from Tuolumne Grove Trailhead and following a fire road near the exit that led to the trail. The trail wasn’t too steep and I was able to keep a brisk pace even with the snow. About half a mile in, I hit the paved road that leads to the lookout, and took that for maybe a mile. This was again a very easy and gradual incline (I think it’s only a ~500 ft elevation gain the whole hike). The road was wide, and very quickly I reached the top of the mountain. The signs ask you not to go up the road to the helipad, so follow the signs down and around, then back up to the lookout tower. From there, there’s a great 360 degree view of the surrounding mountains. I would have loved to stay and watch the sun set from the tower, but because of coronavirus and the current restrictions, you have to be out of the park by 5pm. Since this is a helipad and fire lookout tower, there are a lot of towers, wires, satellite things, etc that can get in the way, so be sure to walk around the entire area to really take in all the scenery. I enjoyed going in winter as this already isn’t a common hike in Yosemite, but other people were few and far between, so it was very peaceful and relaxing of a hike, and a great start to 2021

name: Bill Foy
text: I was associated with this law firm in getting my Work Comp case to take care of my work related injuries. California Workers Compensation is not structured to help the individual who has a claim for ones injuries. It's more in line to help the employers cause. Such is the case that the complainant better have a stable and justifiable injury case. It's a long drawn out process that doesn't add up to get a speedy recovery and get your case placed in your favor and get your well being back where it belongs.  All in all you need a good and caring law firm on your side. It's not easy to find the right law firm. Luckily I did my homework and was able to find the right law firm to get my case closed in my favor. I did the homework for you and I can say if you choose Nantha & Associates Law Offices you'll be in Good Hands too.

name: Crystal K. (Purinmeow)
text:
I went in for a hair cut. I noticed the menu said 32 for a haircut and style. The hair cut and shampoo was cheaper.

Anyway, i went in for a haircut and asked for no style. Just a cut and shampoo.

I was given a stylist who I don't know since I am a walk in. I told her I wanted just a half an inch cut off. She kinda laughed and said something along the lines of "just half an inch?". After she pointed out my hair being damaged I agreed on an inch.

I have never seen anyone cut my hair the way she did.  She had my hair behind my back and bent down to trim my hair.

Every stylist I've had before brought the hair up with their comb layer by layer to cut.

It's as if she literally just straightened my hair with her fingers behind my back, trimmed the ends, and finished. All in under 5 minutes.

I was charged 32 dollars for a 10 dollar hair cut. And i felt insulted by the way she laughed at me for not wanting to cut off more hair.

I would rather pay more money for someone who won't insult me for the hair cut I want and who will spend more time on my hair. Either that or go to a place that charges me fairly for the service they give.

resp.text: We are sorry that you had bad experience with your visit. We would like to address your concerns with the best of our ability. Our office opens at 9 am. You were signed in electronically at 9:17 am.  We see that you left this review at 9:26 am. We are not assigned as your son's Primary Care Physician (PCP). We offered to help you call the insurance to change the PCP, but you left the office at 09:26 am saying that you don't have time to change the PCP. Our office is one stop shop for all your kid's medical needs. We do the school and sports physicals, treat sick kids, provide referrals, evaluate and treat ADHD, do circumcisions, fills forms and provide vaccination in our clinic itself. As a matter of fact, we even help other doctors by providing vaccination for their patients. We do charge the nominal fee of $10 for filling forms as this is not covered by the insurances. Regarding the fine for missed appointment, we had several instances where patients book appointment and don't call to cancel the appointment. This takes away the appointment slots of other patients. It is a huge waste of time and resources for the medical staff and doctors. Even if the patients call few hours prior to their appointment to cancel the appointment we don't charge this fee. Also, we never refused to see any patients if they could not pay this fine. We strive to keep our office exceptionally clean and hygienic, but will continue to improve based on your review. I hope you consider the circumstances under which you had this bad experiences.  Thank you. - Management, Sunshine Pediatrics.

name: Steve Willson
text:
We have been with Farmers/Dan Young's insurance since 1985.
Our house was still standing after the Paradise California Campfire occurred November 8th, 2018.
However we were displaced for 35 days in our RV and lost two outbuildings along with considerable exterior damages totaling sixty thousand dollars.
The Farmers field adjuster was responsive and professional.
We received payment for our fire damage claims right away.
Comparing our experience with Farmers insurance to some of our neighbors experience with their own insurance showed us that choosing the right insurance company and the proper coverage is of the utmost importance.
We recommend Farmers.  They came through for us without fuss and provided outstanding service.
Thank you to Farmers and Dan Young.

text: Very nice family owned jewelry and watch repair shop. Very reasonable prices, quick work. The family is extremely pleasant. Great prices on getting watches up and running. name: Shondra J
text:
The BEST! They are fantastic to work with and I am so happy we discovered them.

As we approached a milestone anniversary,  we were looking at options to enhance my wedding set.  We took my ring to Zales for a repair and while we waited for the estimate, we browsed the cases.  We explained to the salesperson the desire to enhance my ring and we were frustrated that the visit ended with the repair bill exceeding $800 and the salesperson trying to talk us into trading in my wedding to upgrade to a new set. Thankfully we ended up at Michael's Jewelers. The repair to my ring was less than $75 and Victoria spent lots of time helping me design a perfect ring to enhance my current wedding set, without changing my original set. She is extremely knowledgeable and offered some great advice. The finished product was more perfect than I ever imagined.

After our success with my ring, we turned to Victoria to help my son create a beautiful wedding ring out of one of my earrings. She helped capture all of his "wants" and the end product was stunning.

Their prices are reasonable and the quality is superb. We have purchased items, designed jewelry with them, trusted them with our repairs, and plenty of rings cleaned there.  I highly recommend Michael's Jewelers for all of your jewelry needs.
