name: Niema Moshiri
text:
El Guero 2 is an amazing taco shop! I haven't ordered individual plates yet (hopefully soon!), but I have ordered catering from them for our large event (70+ people), and I was blown away. The food was all absolutely delicious and very authentic, and the catering service was excellent. I ordered Take-Out style, but I was told they also can send a taquero to your event.

We ordered adobada, carne asada, pollo asado, shrimp, and veggie, and we got a 5 gallon jug of horchata. Everything was absolutely delicious and perfectly seasoned/marinated, but my personal favorite was by far the adobada, which was cooked to perfection (I feel like many places overcook it). The salsas were also great: it came with pico de gallo, salsa roja, salsa de chipotle, and a mild salsa. Beans, rice, guacamole, and fresh corn tortillas as well.

You can be sure that we'll be ordering from El Guero 2 for plenty more of our events! Thank you, Javier!

name: Clayton Toller
text:
When I originally purchased my home in RWC I had many of the windows replaced with double pane vinyl replacement windows. My window contractor got the Milgard windows from Bennett and I liked them. Over the past few years as we have done remodels and additions I have ordered 1-2 windows/doors at a time from Bennett and the experience has been good each time. You can get any size door or window custom ordered with a 2-3 week lead time. They have moulding packages and skylight systems as well.

Only negative is that parking on the small dead end road is EXTREMELY DIFFICULT.  Bennett glass has 2 diagonal spots that you can't see until you drive to the end. If they are full and you drive a large truck the turnaround can be tricky. I recommend parking 1 street over to look or order and then just pull in the driveway to pick up.

resp.text:
The whole team want to thank you for your long term business and detailed review Clayton! I am glad to hear of your many positive experiences with us at Bennett. Through the test of time, we are your local family owned window and door supplier.

Admittedly, it can get tight in our small corner of Redwood City. For your next visit, there is a narrow alley way exit at the end of the street that can get you back out to Winslow 😊

text:
People know their mechanical stuff here, but it's really expensive. I suggest you should not do an oil regular/synthetic change here because it is really pricey. They charged me $100s for a simple synthetic oil change(Not Mobil 1). I could have done it with other auto shop for $65 per 4-6months. Unfortunately, my car oil engine light was on. I had no choice because I did not want to risk it.

Still, they serve your car pretty well. Just the expensive cost is the problem for me. If you have lots of money, this is your place.

text: I have been here twice and the staff takes extra measures to ensure everyone is safe, especially during this pandemic.  The place is clean and the staff is very efficient and friendly. I love that they send a text message for you to check in online. I didn't wait too long and had a very pleasant experience. I also love that I received an email with a log in to view my images.  Excellent staff, service and state of the art facility!

text: I have been here several times. They are always friendly and accommodating. Yes there is usually a full waiting room, but it moves quickly. The techs are always sensitive and understanding...not rush rush

resp.text: We are extremely disappointed that you didn't have a good experience at our office. We would like to hear more about your visit in order to give us an opportunity to address what went wrong, if you have the time, please email us directly at info@imaginghealthcare.com

name: Louise
text: I was told on phone my appointment was scheduled for 6 PM.  Office staff greeted me but no other conversation. After waiting 45 min, I asked if my appointment was at 6. She said "6:30"....again, no conversation except "he'll be with you shortly." It was another 20 min before I was called back. The tech was unfriendly and unsympathetic that I was apprehensive about having an MRI. Did not explain anything or communicate in any friendly way. The person after me had the same problem. He was told his appointment was 1/2 hour before it actually was. This is not a friendly place to go for any kind of imaging, I will not go back!

name: Kayce P
text: After reading recent reviews, I wanted to share that I actually had a great experience with them. I've spoken to Kathy (twice) on the phone and she's been very pleasant & helpful. My Dr referred me to Tri City for xrays, but I didn't want to go there. IHS accepted walk ins and the woman who checked me in was very nice and friendly. I gave my insurance card and paid less than what I expected for it. Arrival to departure time was less than 20 mins. All staff were friendly and helpful. I have to go back and get copies of my films for a specialist and am able to go outside of normal business hours since they're open later. I know they have other locations, but so far, the Oceanside one has been great.

name: Michael Ries
text:
Lived here from 2017 -2018, and miss it! What a great location, quick access to the highways, jamboree, and equal distance between core areas of Irvine, Costa Mesa, and Newport. They’ve clearly updated the facilities since then, including the addition of W/D in units and a new gym.

If I could, I’d move back down and into these in a heart beat.

resp.text: Thank you for reaching out and sharing your feedback, Michael! We love hearing that we provided a 5-star experience throughout your residency with us. We hope to welcome you back to Irvine Company Apartment Communities again soon! Kindest Regards, The Newport North team

name: Robert Gramlich
text: I really enjoyed my 2 years at Newport North. The upgraded units are amazing. The staff is very friendly.  The amenities are phenomenal. All in all, my favorite place to have lived thus far.

resp.text: We appreciate your feedback, Robert! We are so happy to hear that our team provided a 5-star experience. Thank you for choosing Irvine Company Apartment Communities as your home for two years! Kind Regards, The Newport North team

name: Byung Kim
text:
It was nice living here (4 years ago). Free printing at the office (which is great for certain people like me), and plenty of parking while I was there.

And one huge plus: they had workers with quiet electric equipment. No more getting woken up by loud leaf blowers at 8am in the morning.

resp.text:
Hello Byung,

Thank you so much for taking the time to share your personal experience with us. We are so happy to hear how much you loved your home and that we exceeded your expectations for rental living. Although you have moved away your feedback is still very important to us. Please do not hesitate to contact our Resident Services Office directly if there is ever anything we can do to improve. Have a wonderful week!

Kind Regards,
Newport North Team

name: Andreas Gregory
text: Very noisy place. Noise from everywhere and paper thin windows that don't block anything. The AC units are very old, work constantly and make a lot of noise. They will tell you that they remodeled but they just did the carpet and paint! Management doesn't care and if you request to leave they will hold you on the lease for the remaining term. Very bad!

resp.text: We appreciate you bringing these concerns to our attention, Andreas. We encourage all residents to contact Courtesy Patrol for any neighboring noise concerns in our community, so we may address them as soon as possible. We would like to address your experience further. Please do not hesitate to reach out to our Resident Services Office so we may answer any questions you may have. Best, The Newport North team
